{"term": "1981", "caseName": "McElroy v. United States", "caseLink": "https://www.oyez.org/cases/1981/80-6680", "caseTranscripts": [{"transcriptTitle": "Oral Argument - January 12, 1982", "transcriptLink": "https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/burger8/oral_argument_audio/18094", "transcript": [{"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "We will hear arguments next in McElroy against the United States.", "start": 0, "stop": 5.802, "duration": 5.8, "cleanText": [["we", "will", "hear", "argument", "next", "in", "mcelroy", "against", "the", "united", "state"]]}, {"text": "Mr. White, I think you may proceed whenever you are ready.", "start": 5.802, "stop": 52.599, "duration": 46.8, "cleanText": [["mr", "white", "i", "think", "you", "may", "proceed", "whenever", "you", "be", "ready"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Chief Justice Burger, may it please the Court, this case involves the question of statutory construction of the third paragraph of Section 2314.", "start": 52.599, "stop": 64.74, "duration": 12.14, "cleanText": [["chief", "justice", "burger", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court", "this", "case", "involve", "the", "question", "of", "statutory", "construction", "of", "the", "third", "paragraph", "of", "section"]]}, {"text": "That statute provides in its pertinent part", "start": 64.74, "stop": 71.096, "duration": 6.36, "cleanText": [["that", "statute", "provide", "in", "its", "pertinent", "part"]]}, {"text": "\"Whoever with unlawful or fraudulent intent transports in interstate or foreign commerce any falsely made, forged, altered, or counterfeited securities, knowing the same to have been falsely made, forged, altered, or counterfeited, shall be fined not more than $10,000 or imprisoned not more than ten years or both. \"", "start": 71.096, "stop": 95.045, "duration": 23.95, "cleanText": [["whoever", "with", "unlawful", "or", "fraudulent", "intent", "transport", "in", "interstate", "or", "foreign", "commerce", "any", "falsely", "make", "forge", "alter", "or", "counterfeit", "security", "know", "the", "same", "to", "have", "be", "falsely", "make", "forge", "alter", "or", "counterfeit", "shall", "be", "fin", "not", "more", "than", "or", "imprison", "not", "more", "than", "ten", "year", "or", "both"]]}, {"text": "It is the petitioner's position here that in order for the United States to sustain a valid conviction under this section of the statute, and under this particular paragraph, it is necessary that they prove beyond a reasonable doubt that the check or checks that were here involved in this case be in a forged or altered condition prior to their interstate transportation.", "start": 95.045, "stop": 126.647, "duration": 31.6, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "petitioner", "s", "position", "here", "that", "in", "order", "for", "the", "united", "state", "to", "sustain", "a", "valid", "conviction", "under", "this", "section", "of", "the", "statute", "and", "under", "this", "particular", "paragraph", "it", "be", "necessary", "that", "they", "prove", "beyond", "a", "reasonable", "doubt", "that", "the", "check", "or", "check", "that", "we", "be", "here", "involve", "in", "this", "case", "be", "in", "a", "forged", "or", "altered", "condition", "prior", "to", "their", "interstate", "transportation"]]}, {"text": "If I may briefly state the facts, the petitioner here was indicted on a three-count indict, one count charging him with violation of the Dyer Act, the other two counts charging him with violation of this subsection of 2314.", "start": 126.647, "stop": 145.644, "duration": 19, "cleanText": [["if", "i", "may", "briefly", "state", "the", "fact", "the", "petitioner", "here", "be", "indict", "on", "a", "three", "count", "indict", "one", "count", "charge", "him", "with", "violation", "of", "the", "dyer", "act", "the", "other", "two", "count", "charge", "him", "with", "violation", "of", "this", "subsection", "of"]]}, {"text": "The facts as developed at the trial were as follows.", "start": 145.644, "stop": 150.262, "duration": 4.62, "cleanText": [["the", "fact", "as", "develop", "at", "the", "trial", "we", "be", "as", "follow"]]}, {"text": "Early in 1977, a robbery occurred at the union office in Youngstown, Ohio.", "start": 150.262, "stop": 159.802, "duration": 9.54, "cleanText": [["early", "in", "a", "robbery", "occur", "at", "the", "union", "office", "in", "youngstown", "ohio"]]}, {"text": "Some blank checks were taken.", "start": 159.802, "stop": 161.154, "duration": 1.35, "cleanText": [["some", "blank", "check", "we", "be", "take"]]}, {"text": "The union notified the bank on which the checks were drawn, and the account was closed.", "start": 161.154, "stop": 168.491, "duration": 7.34, "cleanText": [["the", "union", "notify", "the", "bank", "on", "which", "the", "check", "we", "be", "draw", "and", "the", "account", "be", "close"]]}, {"text": "Approximately 17 months later, the petitioner visited an automobile agency in Pittsburgh, Don Allen's Chevrolet, and negotiated the price of a used Corvette.", "start": 168.491, "stop": 183.834, "duration": 15.34, "cleanText": [["approximately", "month", "later", "the", "petitioner", "visit", "an", "automobile", "agency", "in", "pittsburgh", "don", "allen", "s", "chevrolet", "and", "negotiate", "the", "price", "of", "a", "used", "corvette"]]}, {"text": "After arriving at the price, he told the man, the salesman that he would be back the next day, that he lived in Ohio, that he had to get a check from his credit union.", "start": 183.834, "stop": 198.76, "duration": 14.93, "cleanText": [["after", "arrive", "at", "the", "price", "he", "tell", "the", "man", "the", "salesman", "that", "he", "would", "be", "back", "the", "next", "day", "that", "he", "live", "in", "ohio", "that", "he", "have", "to", "get", "a", "check", "from", "his", "credit", "union"]]}, {"text": "He also told him that he worked in the Pittsburgh area for a railroad.", "start": 198.76, "stop": 202.728, "duration": 3.97, "cleanText": [["he", "also", "tell", "him", "that", "he", "work", "in", "the", "pittsburgh", "area", "for", "a", "railroad"]]}, {"text": "The next day he appeared with one of the checks that had been stolen at the union office in Youngstown, and it was... when he presented it, it was altered and forged.", "start": 202.728, "stop": 216.972, "duration": 14.24, "cleanText": [["the", "next", "day", "he", "appear", "with", "one", "of", "the", "check", "that", "have", "be", "steal", "at", "the", "union", "office", "in", "youngstown", "and", "it", "be", "when", "he", "present", "it", "it", "be", "alter", "and", "forge"]]}, {"text": "The dealership took possession of the check, and he took possession of the car.", "start": 216.972, "stop": 223.459, "duration": 6.49, "cleanText": [["the", "dealership", "take", "possession", "of", "the", "check", "and", "he", "take", "possession", "of", "the", "car"]]}, {"text": "The car was never found again.", "start": 223.459, "stop": 224.876, "duration": 1.42, "cleanText": [["the", "car", "be", "never", "find", "again"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "You say, when he presented it, it was altered and forged.", "start": 224.876, "stop": 229.529, "duration": 4.65, "cleanText": [["you", "say", "when", "he", "present", "it", "it", "be", "alter", "and", "forge"]]}, {"text": "Do you mean by that that the forgery and alteration had taken place prior to the presentation?", "start": 229.529, "stop": 237.199, "duration": 7.67, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "mean", "by", "that", "that", "the", "forgery", "and", "alteration", "have", "take", "place", "prior", "to", "the", "presentation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 237.199, "stop": 239.051, "duration": 1.85, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "That occurred, of course, in Pittsburgh.", "start": 239.051, "stop": 242.67, "duration": 3.62, "cleanText": [["that", "occur", "of", "course", "in", "pittsburgh"]]}, {"text": "The second--", "start": 242.67, "stop": 246.122, "duration": 3.45, "cleanText": [["the", "second"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "But I gather the alteration or forgery occurred in the state of Pennsylvania, did it?", "start": 246.122, "stop": 251.026, "duration": 4.9, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "gather", "the", "alteration", "or", "forgery", "occur", "in", "the", "state", "of", "pennsylvania", "do", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, that is the question, Your Honor.", "start": 251.026, "stop": 252.978, "duration": 1.95, "cleanText": [["well", "that", "be", "the", "question", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "We believe that there is a presumption that works here, that when a check is presented that is a forgery, that there is a presumption that it was forged where it first appeared.", "start": 252.978, "stop": 266.369, "duration": 13.39, "cleanText": [["we", "believe", "that", "there", "be", "a", "presumption", "that", "work", "here", "that", "when", "a", "check", "be", "present", "that", "be", "a", "forgery", "that", "there", "be", "a", "presumption", "that", "it", "be", "forge", "where", "it", "first", "appear"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Where do you get that from?", "start": 266.369, "stop": 267.519, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["where", "do", "you", "get", "that", "from"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, that is a presumption that goes back to 1822, Justice Storey, and it has been utilized by the lower federal courts.", "start": 267.519, "stop": 277.926, "duration": 10.41, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "that", "be", "a", "presumption", "that", "go", "back", "to", "justice", "storey", "and", "it", "have", "be", "utilize", "by", "the", "low", "federal", "court"]]}, {"text": "One of the courts that utilized it was one of the courts of which... which would cause the split here among the circuits, Owens versus the United States.", "start": 277.926, "stop": 288.215, "duration": 10.29, "cleanText": [["one", "of", "the", "court", "that", "utilize", "it", "be", "one", "of", "the", "court", "of", "which", "which", "would", "because", "the", "split", "here", "among", "the", "circuit", "owens", "versus", "the", "united", "state"]]}, {"text": "The Fifth Circuit relied on that.", "start": 288.215, "stop": 290.751, "duration": 2.54, "cleanText": [["the", "fifth", "circuit", "rely", "on", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Was Justice Storey talking about the criminal law area?", "start": 290.751, "stop": 293.936, "duration": 3.19, "cleanText": [["be", "justice", "storey", "talk", "about", "the", "criminal", "law", "area"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor, he was, and it was used in that case to establish venue.", "start": 293.936, "stop": 299.84, "duration": 5.9, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor", "he", "be", "and", "it", "be", "use", "in", "that", "case", "to", "establish", "venue"]]}, {"text": "The second incident occurred at Rini Boat Sales in Beaver Falls, Pennsylvania.", "start": 299.84, "stop": 308.244, "duration": 8.4, "cleanText": [["the", "second", "incident", "occur", "at", "rini", "boat", "sale", "in", "beaver", "fall", "pennsylvania"]]}, {"text": "Again the petitioner appeared, negotiated the price of a boat with a trailer to haul it away, and after having agreed on the price, he told them that he lived in Ohio, and that he had to get a check from his credit union.", "start": 308.244, "stop": 327.573, "duration": 19.33, "cleanText": [["again", "the", "petitioner", "appear", "negotiate", "the", "price", "of", "a", "boat", "with", "a", "trailer", "to", "haul", "it", "away", "and", "after", "have", "agree", "on", "the", "price", "he", "tell", "them", "that", "he", "live", "in", "ohio", "and", "that", "he", "have", "to", "get", "a", "check", "from", "his", "credit", "union"]]}, {"text": "About a week later he telephoned them, told them that he had the funds, and that he would be there some time during that day, but he had to work overtime.", "start": 327.573, "stop": 337.279, "duration": 9.71, "cleanText": [["about", "a", "week", "later", "he", "telephone", "them", "tell", "them", "that", "he", "have", "the", "fund", "and", "that", "he", "would", "be", "there", "some", "time", "during", "that", "day", "but", "he", "have", "to", "work", "overtime"]]}, {"text": "About a few hours later he called and told them he was on the Ohio Turnpike, at a rest stop, and he would be there shortly.", "start": 337.279, "stop": 347.321, "duration": 10.04, "cleanText": [["about", "a", "few", "hour", "later", "he", "call", "and", "tell", "them", "he", "be", "on", "the", "ohio", "turnpike", "at", "a", "rest", "stop", "and", "he", "would", "be", "there", "shortly"]]}, {"text": "Approximately 20 minutes later, an employee of Rini Boat Sales was standing in front of the agency, when he saw the petitioner pull out of a dead end street in a pickup truck.", "start": 347.321, "stop": 363.263, "duration": 15.94, "cleanText": [["approximately", "minute", "later", "an", "employee", "of", "rini", "boat", "sale", "be", "stand", "in", "front", "of", "the", "agency", "when", "he", "saw", "the", "petitioner", "pull", "out", "of", "a", "dead", "end", "street", "in", "a", "pickup", "truck"]]}, {"text": "What followed then was just what happened at the Chevrolet agency.", "start": 363.263, "stop": 368.298, "duration": 5.04, "cleanText": [["what", "follow", "then", "be", "just", "what", "happen", "at", "the", "chevrolet", "agency"]]}, {"text": "The dealer took possession of a check that was in a forged and altered condition.", "start": 368.298, "stop": 373, "duration": 4.7, "cleanText": [["the", "dealer", "take", "possession", "of", "a", "check", "that", "be", "in", "a", "forged", "and", "altered", "condition"]]}, {"text": "It was one of the checks that had been stolen at the union office in Youngstown 17 months previously.", "start": 373, "stop": 380.106, "duration": 7.11, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "one", "of", "the", "check", "that", "have", "be", "steal", "at", "the", "union", "office", "in", "youngstown", "month", "previously"]]}, {"text": "And thereafter, the boat and the trailer were taken by the petitioner.", "start": 380.106, "stop": 385.241, "duration": 5.13, "cleanText": [["and", "thereafter", "the", "boat", "and", "the", "trailer", "we", "be", "take", "by", "the", "petitioner"]]}, {"text": "The boat was found about a year later in Pennsylvania.", "start": 385.241, "stop": 387.943, "duration": 2.7, "cleanText": [["the", "boat", "be", "find", "about", "a", "year", "later", "in", "pennsylvania"]]}, {"text": "At the conclusion of the evidence, the defendant moved for a judgment of acquittal on the grounds that there was no evidence to support the Dyer Act count because there was no evidence to show that the Corvette had been taken from Pennsylvania to Ohio, and on the check charges, there was insufficient evidence because the government had failed to prove as required by this paragraph of the statute that the checks were in a forged or altered condition prior to their interstate transportation.", "start": 387.943, "stop": 424.468, "duration": 36.53, "cleanText": [["at", "the", "conclusion", "of", "the", "evidence", "the", "defendant", "move", "for", "a", "judgment", "of", "acquittal", "on", "the", "ground", "that", "there", "be", "no", "evidence", "to", "support", "the", "dyer", "act", "count", "because", "there", "be", "no", "evidence", "to", "show", "that", "the", "corvette", "have", "be", "take", "from", "pennsylvania", "to", "ohio", "and", "on", "the", "check", "charge", "there", "be", "insufficient", "evidence", "because", "the", "government", "have", "fail", "to", "prove", "as", "require", "by", "this", "paragraph", "of", "the", "statute", "that", "the", "check", "we", "be", "in", "a", "forged", "or", "altered", "condition", "prior", "to", "their", "interstate", "transportation"]]}, {"text": "The judge denied both the motions, and charged the jury in accordance with the points for charge presented by the government that it was not necessary that the checks be in a forged or altered condition so long as they could show or the jury found that the checks were moving in interstate commerce in a forged or altered condition solely in the destination state.", "start": 424.468, "stop": 454.653, "duration": 30.19, "cleanText": [["the", "judge", "deny", "both", "the", "motion", "and", "charge", "the", "jury", "in", "accordance", "with", "the", "point", "for", "charge", "present", "by", "the", "government", "that", "it", "be", "not", "necessary", "that", "the", "check", "be", "in", "a", "forged", "or", "altered", "condition", "so", "long", "as", "they", "could", "show", "or", "the", "jury", "find", "that", "the", "check", "we", "be", "move", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "in", "a", "forged", "or", "altered", "condition", "solely", "in", "the", "destination", "state"]]}, {"text": "Now, the defendant petitioner here was convicted.", "start": 454.653, "stop": 461.307, "duration": 6.65, "cleanText": [["now", "the", "defendant", "petitioner", "here", "be", "convict"]]}, {"text": "He received a five-year sentence on the Dyer Act count and seven-year sentences on the check counts, all the sentences to run concurrently.", "start": 461.307, "stop": 472.199, "duration": 10.89, "cleanText": [["he", "receive", "a", "five", "year", "sentence", "on", "the", "dyer", "act", "count", "and", "seven", "year", "sentence", "on", "the", "check", "count", "all", "the", "sentence", "to", "run", "concurrently"]]}, {"text": "On appeal to the Third Circuit, they said that there was insufficient evidence to convict on the Dyer Act count, because the indictment charged him with taking the automobile from Ohio... sorry, from Pennsylvania into Ohio, and there was no evidence that the automobile ever went into Ohio.", "start": 472.199, "stop": 494.278, "duration": 22.08, "cleanText": [["on", "appeal", "to", "the", "third", "circuit", "they", "say", "that", "there", "be", "insufficient", "evidence", "to", "convict", "on", "the", "dyer", "act", "count", "because", "the", "indictment", "charge", "him", "with", "take", "the", "automobile", "from", "ohio", "sorry", "from", "pennsylvania", "into", "ohio", "and", "there", "be", "no", "evidence", "that", "the", "automobile", "ever", "go", "into", "ohio"]]}, {"text": "But on the check charges, they said that the judge's charge was correct, and they held chat it was not necessary under this statute for the government to prove that the checks were in a forged or altered condition prior to their interstate transportation and prior to crossing state lines.", "start": 494.278, "stop": 517.394, "duration": 23.12, "cleanText": [["but", "on", "the", "check", "charge", "they", "say", "that", "the", "judge", "s", "charge", "be", "correct", "and", "they", "hold", "chat", "it", "be", "not", "necessary", "under", "this", "statute", "for", "the", "government", "to", "prove", "that", "the", "check", "we", "be", "in", "a", "forged", "or", "altered", "condition", "prior", "to", "their", "interstate", "transportation", "and", "prior", "to", "cross", "state", "line"]]}, {"text": "When they so held that, they held directly in conflict with the Tenth, Eight, and Fifth Circuit Courts of Appeals, which have held with regard to this paragraph of 2314 that it is clear and obvious from a reading of this statute, because of the tenses used and so forth, that this statute means that the--", "start": 517.394, "stop": 542.961, "duration": 25.57, "cleanText": [["when", "they", "so", "hold", "that", "they", "hold", "directly", "in", "conflict", "with", "the", "tenth", "eight", "and", "fifth", "circuit", "court", "of", "appeal", "which", "have", "hold", "with", "regard", "to", "this", "paragraph", "of", "that", "it", "be", "clear", "and", "obvious", "from", "a", "reading", "of", "this", "statute", "because", "of", "the", "tense", "use", "and", "so", "forth", "that", "this", "statute", "mean", "that", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "It is not the whole statute, it is just two words they rely on, right?", "start": 542.961, "stop": 546.413, "duration": 3.45, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "not", "the", "whole", "statute", "it", "be", "just", "two", "word", "they", "rely", "on", "right"]]}, {"text": "\"Have been\"?", "start": 546.413, "stop": 548.113, "duration": 1.7, "cleanText": [["have", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, Your Honor, I think it is... I don't want to say what they had in their mind.", "start": 548.113, "stop": 553.984, "duration": 5.87, "cleanText": [["no", "your", "honor", "i", "think", "it", "be", "i", "do", "not", "want", "to", "say", "what", "they", "have", "in", "their", "mind"]]}, {"text": "They just said a reading is obvious, but I will attempt to--", "start": 553.984, "stop": 557.638, "duration": 3.65, "cleanText": [["they", "just", "say", "a", "reading", "be", "obvious", "but", "i", "will", "attempt", "to"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what other words can you get your argument out of?", "start": 557.638, "stop": 559.838, "duration": 2.2, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "other", "word", "can", "you", "get", "your", "argument", "out", "of"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--\"Forged\", Your Honor.", "start": 559.838, "stop": 561.173, "duration": 1.34, "cleanText": [["forge", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "Past tense.", "start": 561.173, "stop": 562.09, "duration": 0.92, "cleanText": [["past", "tense"]]}, {"text": "The forged checks prior to the interstate transportation.", "start": 562.09, "stop": 566.042, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["the", "forged", "check", "prior", "to", "the", "interstate", "transportation"]]}, {"text": "It is the way the statute--", "start": 566.042, "stop": 567.093, "duration": 1.05, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "way", "the", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "There is nothing that says the check has to be forged before it is transferred.", "start": 567.093, "stop": 570.112, "duration": 3.02, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "nothing", "that", "say", "the", "check", "have", "to", "be", "forge", "before", "it", "be", "transfer"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, it doesn't, Your Honor, but the way the tenses are set up in the structure of the section; we believe that it is clear that Congress intended that, and I will demonstrate that, Your Honor, by the Congressional history.", "start": 570.112, "stop": 584.02, "duration": 13.91, "cleanText": [["no", "it", "do", "not", "your", "honor", "but", "the", "way", "the", "tense", "be", "set", "up", "in", "the", "structure", "of", "the", "section", "we", "believe", "that", "it", "be", "clear", "that", "congress", "intend", "that", "and", "i", "will", "demonstrate", "that", "your", "honor", "by", "the", "congressional", "history"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, if the language of the statute is clear, do we need to go to the legislative history?", "start": 584.02, "stop": 591.19, "duration": 7.17, "cleanText": [["well", "if", "the", "language", "of", "the", "statute", "be", "clear", "do", "we", "need", "to", "go", "to", "the", "legislative", "history"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, if it is clear, you do not, and our first submission here is that it is not ambiguous, it is clear on its face that what it means is that the checks must be in a forged condition before they enter interstate commerce, but our fallback position, Your Honor, and our second position is, if this wording is ambiguous, then this court should utilize the rule of Lenity.", "start": 591.19, "stop": 619.693, "duration": 28.5, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "if", "it", "be", "clear", "you", "do", "not", "and", "our", "first", "submission", "here", "be", "that", "it", "be", "not", "ambiguous", "it", "be", "clear", "on", "its", "face", "that", "what", "it", "mean", "be", "that", "the", "check", "must", "be", "in", "a", "forged", "condition", "before", "they", "enter", "interstate", "commerce", "but", "our", "fallback", "position", "your", "honor", "and", "our", "second", "position", "be", "if", "this", "wording", "be", "ambiguous", "then", "this", "court", "should", "utilize", "the", "rule", "of", "lenity"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you have some cases that say, apply the rule of Lenity in the face of what might be clear legislative history, even though the words are ambiguous?", "start": 619.693, "stop": 628.097, "duration": 8.4, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "have", "some", "case", "that", "say", "apply", "the", "rule", "of", "lenity", "in", "the", "face", "of", "what", "might", "be", "clear", "legislative", "history", "even", "though", "the", "word", "be", "ambiguous"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your honor, you are right.", "start": 628.097, "stop": 630.513, "duration": 2.42, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "you", "be", "right"]]}, {"text": "Of course, you would not thwart the will of Congress if you could show clearly by the legislative history what Congress meant.", "start": 630.513, "stop": 640.821, "duration": 10.31, "cleanText": [["of", "course", "you", "would", "not", "thwart", "the", "will", "of", "congress", "if", "you", "could", "show", "clearly", "by", "the", "legislative", "history", "what", "congress", "meant"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Even though the words themselves might be ambiguous?", "start": 640.821, "stop": 643.107, "duration": 2.29, "cleanText": [["even", "though", "the", "word", "themselves", "might", "be", "ambiguous"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Even though the words might be ambiguous.", "start": 643.107, "stop": 644.873, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["even", "though", "the", "word", "might", "be", "ambiguous"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "But your position is that there is no evidence like that in this case?", "start": 644.873, "stop": 648.761, "duration": 3.89, "cleanText": [["but", "your", "position", "be", "that", "there", "be", "no", "evidence", "like", "that", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "As a matter of fact, there is contrary evidence to sustain our position, Your Honor.", "start": 648.761, "stop": 652.879, "duration": 4.12, "cleanText": [["as", "a", "matter", "of", "fact", "there", "be", "contrary", "evidence", "to", "sustain", "our", "position", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Do you take the position that if you forge a check or a security, and you get across a state line, you are free?", "start": 652.879, "stop": 664.52, "duration": 11.64, "cleanText": [["do", "you", "take", "the", "position", "that", "if", "you", "forge", "a", "check", "or", "a", "security", "and", "you", "get", "across", "a", "state", "line", "you", "be", "free"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "No.", "start": 664.52, "stop": 665.353, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["no"]]}, {"text": "If you forge a check and cross a state line, you are guilty.", "start": 665.353, "stop": 670.84, "duration": 5.49, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "forge", "a", "check", "and", "cross", "a", "state", "line", "you", "be", "guilty"]]}, {"text": "If you take a blank check and cross a state line, and then forge it--", "start": 670.84, "stop": 678.011, "duration": 7.17, "cleanText": [["if", "you", "take", "a", "blank", "check", "and", "cross", "a", "state", "line", "and", "then", "forge", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Then you are free.", "start": 678.011, "stop": 680.03, "duration": 2.02, "cleanText": [["then", "you", "be", "free"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--you have not violated this section.", "start": 680.03, "stop": 680.863, "duration": 0.83, "cleanText": [["you", "have", "not", "violate", "this", "section"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "And you can cross eight other state lines?", "start": 680.863, "stop": 683.148, "duration": 2.28, "cleanText": [["and", "you", "can", "cross", "eight", "other", "state", "line"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, Your Honor.", "start": 683.148, "stop": 684.267, "duration": 1.12, "cleanText": [["no", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "Yes, I think I would say that, if it is a continuous movement.", "start": 684.267, "stop": 688.136, "duration": 3.87, "cleanText": [["yes", "i", "think", "i", "would", "say", "that", "if", "it", "be", "a", "continuous", "movement"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "And then you realize that it doesn't make sense, don't you?", "start": 688.136, "stop": 691.754, "duration": 3.62, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "you", "realize", "that", "it", "do", "not", "make", "sense", "do", "not", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, it does, Your Honor.", "start": 691.754, "stop": 693.04, "duration": 1.29, "cleanText": [["yes", "it", "do", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Congress was against transporting forged securities.", "start": 693.04, "stop": 697.907, "duration": 4.87, "cleanText": [["congress", "be", "against", "transport", "forged", "security"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "You are right, Your Honor, and they took care of that provision.", "start": 697.907, "stop": 701.276, "duration": 3.37, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "right", "your", "honor", "and", "they", "take", "care", "of", "that", "provision"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, this was a forged security, wasn't it?", "start": 701.276, "stop": 702.526, "duration": 1.25, "cleanText": [["well", "this", "be", "a", "forged", "security", "be", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 702.526, "stop": 703.076, "duration": 0.55, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "When it was presented, it was forged, wasn't it?", "start": 703.076, "stop": 705.811, "duration": 2.74, "cleanText": [["when", "it", "be", "present", "it", "be", "forge", "be", "not", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right, Your Honor.", "start": 705.811, "stop": 706.628, "duration": 0.82, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "And it had crossed the state line, right?", "start": 706.628, "stop": 709.513, "duration": 2.88, "cleanText": [["and", "it", "have", "cross", "the", "state", "line", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, not under this section.", "start": 709.513, "stop": 711.882, "duration": 2.37, "cleanText": [["no", "not", "under", "this", "section"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "It had crossed... the check had crossed the state line.", "start": 711.882, "stop": 716.452, "duration": 4.57, "cleanText": [["it", "have", "cross", "the", "check", "have", "cross", "the", "state", "line"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "A blank check.", "start": 716.452, "stop": 717.386, "duration": 0.93, "cleanText": [["a", "blank", "check"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "A check had crossed a state line.", "start": 717.386, "stop": 721.154, "duration": 3.77, "cleanText": [["a", "check", "have", "cross", "a", "state", "line"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "I agree with you.", "start": 721.154, "stop": 722.023, "duration": 0.87, "cleanText": [["i", "agree", "with", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "And when it was presented, it was forged.", "start": 722.023, "stop": 724.39, "duration": 2.37, "cleanText": [["and", "when", "it", "be", "present", "it", "be", "forge"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right, Your Honor.", "start": 724.39, "stop": 725.308, "duration": 0.92, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "And that, in any reading of the statute, violates the statute.", "start": 725.308, "stop": 728.677, "duration": 3.37, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "in", "any", "reading", "of", "the", "statute", "violate", "the", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, Your Honor.", "start": 728.677, "stop": 729.327, "duration": 0.65, "cleanText": [["no", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "May I suggest--", "start": 729.327, "stop": 730.36, "duration": 1.03, "cleanText": [["may", "i", "suggest"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what else is there in the statute that you have to show?", "start": 730.36, "stop": 733.129, "duration": 2.77, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "else", "be", "there", "in", "the", "statute", "that", "you", "have", "to", "show"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Okay.", "start": 733.129, "stop": 733.612, "duration": 0.48, "cleanText": [["okay"]]}, {"text": "Your Honor, may I suggest that Congress when they passed this Act, the National Stolen Properties Act, took care of the situation that the defendant was here charged with.", "start": 733.612, "stop": 745.835, "duration": 12.22, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "may", "i", "suggest", "that", "congress", "when", "they", "pass", "this", "act", "the", "national", "stolen", "property", "act", "take", "care", "of", "the", "situation", "that", "the", "defendant", "be", "here", "charge", "with"]]}, {"text": "They took care of it in Section 4, which now became Section 2315, which provides with regard to the same activity,", "start": 745.835, "stop": 759.81, "duration": 13.97, "cleanText": [["they", "take", "care", "of", "it", "in", "section", "which", "now", "become", "section", "which", "provide", "with", "regard", "to", "the", "same", "activity"]]}, {"text": "\"Whoever receives, conceals, stores, barters, sells, or disposes of any falsely made, forged, altered, or counterfeited securities moving as or which are a part of or which constitute interstate or foreign commerce. \"", "start": 759.81, "stop": 780.223, "duration": 20.41, "cleanText": [["whoever", "receive", "conceals", "store", "barter", "sell", "or", "disposes", "of", "any", "falsely", "make", "forge", "alter", "or", "counterfeit", "security", "move", "as", "or", "which", "be", "a", "part", "of", "or", "which", "constitute", "interstate", "or", "foreign", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "We submit, Your Honor, that the whole problem in this case is strictly this, that the government failed to indict him under the right section.", "start": 780.223, "stop": 791.964, "duration": 11.74, "cleanText": [["we", "submit", "your", "honor", "that", "the", "whole", "problem", "in", "this", "case", "be", "strictly", "this", "that", "the", "government", "fail", "to", "indict", "him", "under", "the", "right", "section"]]}, {"text": "Had they charged him under 2315, it would have fit the facts.", "start": 791.964, "stop": 797.935, "duration": 5.97, "cleanText": [["have", "they", "charge", "him", "under", "it", "would", "have", "fit", "the", "fact"]]}, {"text": "Having charged him under 2314, they then tried to pull themselves up, and act like Procrusteas, and try to stretch the language of 2314 to make it fit a situation which was governed by 2315.", "start": 797.935, "stop": 815.897, "duration": 17.96, "cleanText": [["have", "charge", "him", "under", "they", "then", "try", "to", "pull", "themselves", "up", "and", "act", "like", "procrusteas", "and", "try", "to", "stretch", "the", "language", "of", "to", "make", "it", "fit", "a", "situation", "which", "be", "govern", "by"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "You would say, I take it, or would you, if there was a question, would you say that the proof would have been satisfied in this kind of a case if the statute, after the word", "start": 815.897, "stop": 828.537, "duration": 12.64, "cleanText": [["you", "would", "say", "i", "take", "it", "or", "would", "you", "if", "there", "be", "a", "question", "would", "you", "say", "that", "the", "proof", "would", "have", "be", "satisfy", "in", "this", "kind", "of", "a", "case", "if", "the", "statute", "after", "the", "word"]]}, {"text": "\"transports in interstate or foreign commerce. \"", "start": 828.537, "stop": 832.072, "duration": 3.53, "cleanText": [["transport", "in", "interstate", "or", "foreign", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "any \"stolen\", insert the word \"stolen\", comma, \"falsely made\", comma, \"forged\", comma, \"altered\"?", "start": 832.072, "stop": 840.345, "duration": 8.27, "cleanText": [["any", "stolen", "insert", "the", "word", "steal", "comma", "falsely", "make", "comma", "forge", "comma", "alter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "It would have taken care of it, and they did in the first paragraph, Your Honor.", "start": 840.345, "stop": 844.297, "duration": 3.95, "cleanText": [["it", "would", "have", "take", "care", "of", "it", "and", "they", "do", "in", "the", "first", "paragraph", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "You see, in the first paragraph of the statute, it provides against the interstate transportation of stolen merchandise, but Congress has a $5,000 limit.", "start": 844.297, "stop": 856.872, "duration": 12.57, "cleanText": [["you", "see", "in", "the", "first", "paragraph", "of", "the", "statute", "it", "provide", "against", "the", "interstate", "transportation", "of", "stolen", "merchandise", "but", "congress", "have", "a", "limit"]]}, {"text": "Now, I don't want to concede that he could have been convicted under that statute, but both of these checks were over $5,000.", "start": 856.872, "stop": 865.377, "duration": 8.5, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "do", "not", "want", "to", "concede", "that", "he", "could", "have", "be", "convict", "under", "that", "statute", "but", "both", "of", "these", "check", "we", "be", "over"]]}, {"text": "I simply find in this case that the government charged him under the wrong statute.", "start": 865.377, "stop": 872.983, "duration": 7.61, "cleanText": [["i", "simply", "find", "in", "this", "case", "that", "the", "government", "charge", "him", "under", "the", "wrong", "statute"]]}, {"text": "The legislative history--", "start": 872.983, "stop": 874.899, "duration": 1.92, "cleanText": [["the", "legislative", "history"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Let me ask you, is the section you are relying on the section at the bottom of Page 13 of your brief, the section... that is the one you are talking about, 2314?", "start": 874.899, "stop": 886.291, "duration": 11.39, "cleanText": [["let", "me", "ask", "you", "be", "the", "section", "you", "be", "rely", "on", "the", "section", "at", "the", "bottom", "of", "page", "of", "your", "brief", "the", "section", "that", "be", "the", "one", "you", "be", "talk", "about"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 886.291, "stop": 887.074, "duration": 0.78, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "That doesn't refer to forged securities, though, does it?", "start": 887.074, "stop": 889.326, "duration": 2.25, "cleanText": [["that", "do", "not", "refer", "to", "forge", "security", "though", "do", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 889.326, "stop": 890.393, "duration": 1.07, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "In the paragraph, second paragraph of 2315, Your Honor, the reading is almost exactly the same.", "start": 890.393, "stop": 899.432, "duration": 9.04, "cleanText": [["in", "the", "paragraph", "second", "paragraph", "of", "your", "honor", "the", "reading", "be", "almost", "exactly", "the", "same"]]}, {"text": "\"Whoever receives, conceals, stores, barters-- \"", "start": 899.432, "stop": 902.317, "duration": 2.88, "cleanText": [["whoever", "receive", "conceals", "store", "barter"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Where are you reading?", "start": 902.317, "stop": 902.919, "duration": 0.6, "cleanText": [["where", "be", "you", "read"]]}, {"text": "That is what I want to know.", "start": 902.919, "stop": 903.769, "duration": 0.85, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "what", "i", "want", "to", "know"]]}, {"text": "What is it you are quoting from?", "start": 903.769, "stop": 905.454, "duration": 1.68, "cleanText": [["what", "be", "it", "you", "be", "quote", "from"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I am quoting from--", "start": 905.454, "stop": 906.787, "duration": 1.33, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "quote", "from"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "I mean, it is not in the brief.", "start": 906.787, "stop": 907.404, "duration": 0.62, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "it", "be", "not", "in", "the", "brief"]]}, {"text": "Is that right?", "start": 907.404, "stop": 907.987, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["be", "that", "right"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, Your Honor.", "start": 907.987, "stop": 908.572, "duration": 0.59, "cleanText": [["no", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, I am sorry.", "start": 908.572, "stop": 909.106, "duration": 0.53, "cleanText": [["oh", "i", "be", "sorry"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "We don't have that whole statute set out, Your Honor, but it is in the second paragraph of 2315.", "start": 909.106, "stop": 916.143, "duration": 7.04, "cleanText": [["we", "do", "not", "have", "that", "whole", "statute", "set", "out", "your", "honor", "but", "it", "be", "in", "the", "second", "paragraph", "of"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "I see.", "start": 916.143, "stop": 917.226, "duration": 1.08, "cleanText": [["i", "see"]]}, {"text": "Is it possible to violate two Acts?", "start": 917.226, "stop": 919.095, "duration": 1.87, "cleanText": [["be", "it", "possible", "to", "violate", "two", "act"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor, you could do that.", "start": 919.095, "stop": 923.547, "duration": 4.45, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor", "you", "could", "do", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "I am just wondering.", "start": 923.547, "stop": 924.397, "duration": 0.85, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "just", "wondering"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor, but they didn't charge him with 2315.", "start": 924.397, "stop": 927.765, "duration": 3.37, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor", "but", "they", "do", "not", "charge", "him", "with"]]}, {"text": "That has been the whole point.", "start": 927.765, "stop": 928.617, "duration": 0.85, "cleanText": [["that", "have", "be", "the", "whole", "point"]]}, {"text": "And as the dissenter pointed out in the court of appeals in the en banc decision, they could have also probably convicted this man under section... under the last paragraph of 2314.", "start": 928.617, "stop": 944.711, "duration": 16.09, "cleanText": [["and", "as", "the", "dissenter", "point", "out", "in", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "in", "the", "en", "banc", "decision", "they", "could", "have", "also", "probably", "convict", "this", "man", "under", "section", "under", "the", "last", "paragraph", "of"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "I'll bet there are a lot of other things he could be convicted of, too.", "start": 944.711, "stop": 945.995, "duration": 1.28, "cleanText": [["I", "will", "bet", "there", "be", "a", "lot", "of", "other", "thing", "he", "could", "be", "convict", "of", "too"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's right, many others.", "start": 945.995, "stop": 947.479, "duration": 1.48, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "right", "many", "others"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Oh, you agree?", "start": 947.479, "stop": 948.062, "duration": 0.58, "cleanText": [["oh", "you", "agree"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 948.062, "stop": 949.297, "duration": 1.24, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "But there is no question under this particular section of the statute that he was not validly convicted.", "start": 949.297, "stop": 958.386, "duration": 9.09, "cleanText": [["but", "there", "be", "no", "question", "under", "this", "particular", "section", "of", "the", "statute", "that", "he", "be", "not", "validly", "convict"]]}, {"text": "When Congress passed the National Stolen Properties Act, they did not rely on the words \"interstate commerce\" as defined by this Court.", "start": 958.386, "stop": 975.182, "duration": 16.8, "cleanText": [["when", "congress", "pass", "the", "national", "stolen", "property", "act", "they", "do", "not", "rely", "on", "the", "word", "interstate", "commerce", "as", "define", "by", "this", "court"]]}, {"text": "The government attempts to show that by going back to the Dyer Act, and it says they can't find anything that would indicate the will of Congress with regard to the National Stolen Properties Act.", "start": 975.182, "stop": 986.554, "duration": 11.37, "cleanText": [["the", "government", "attempt", "to", "show", "that", "by", "go", "back", "to", "the", "dyer", "act", "and", "it", "say", "they", "can", "not", "find", "anything", "that", "would", "indicate", "the", "will", "of", "congress", "with", "regard", "to", "the", "national", "stolen", "property", "act"]]}, {"text": "Your Honor, when the National Stolen Property Act was passed, Congress put their own definition of interstate commerce into the statute, and they didn't give anybody any leeway to interpret it.", "start": 986.554, "stop": 1003.582, "duration": 17.03, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "when", "the", "national", "stolen", "property", "act", "be", "pass", "congress", "put", "their", "own", "definition", "of", "interstate", "commerce", "into", "the", "statute", "and", "they", "do", "not", "give", "anybody", "any", "leeway", "to", "interpret", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. White, certainly in the Tobin case and in the Barfield case, the parallel language in the adjacent two statutes has been interpreted exactly as the government is asking that it be interpreted here.", "start": 1003.582, "stop": 1020.877, "duration": 17.29, "cleanText": [["mr", "white", "certainly", "in", "the", "tobin", "case", "and", "in", "the", "barfield", "case", "the", "parallel", "language", "in", "the", "adjacent", "two", "statute", "have", "be", "interpret", "exactly", "as", "the", "government", "be", "ask", "that", "it", "be", "interpret", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, I think--", "start": 1020.877, "stop": 1021.793, "duration": 0.92, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "i", "think"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "How do you distinguish that?", "start": 1021.793, "stop": 1023.377, "duration": 1.58, "cleanText": [["how", "do", "you", "distinguish", "that"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Because of the \"moving as\" language, Your Honor.", "start": 1023.377, "stop": 1026.179, "duration": 2.8, "cleanText": [["because", "of", "the", "moving", "as", "language", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "It is clear that", "start": 1026.179, "stop": 1027.695, "duration": 1.52, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "clear", "that"]]}, {"text": "\"moving as, constituting a part of interstate commerce. \"", "start": 1027.695, "stop": 1030.714, "duration": 3.02, "cleanText": [["moving", "as", "constitute", "a", "part", "of", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "is different than having an act that is committed prior to the transportation in interstate commerce.", "start": 1030.714, "stop": 1038.32, "duration": 7.61, "cleanText": [["be", "different", "than", "have", "an", "act", "that", "be", "commit", "prior", "to", "the", "transportation", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "That is what I think the whole Act was... these two sections were designed to do, and remember, 2314 and 2315 were one section in the National Stolen Properties Act.", "start": 1038.32, "stop": 1050.127, "duration": 11.81, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "what", "i", "think", "the", "whole", "act", "be", "these", "two", "section", "we", "be", "design", "to", "do", "and", "remember", "and", "we", "be", "one", "section", "in", "the", "national", "stolen", "property", "act"]]}, {"text": "But this definition that Congress put in provided as follows.", "start": 1050.127, "stop": 1057.698, "duration": 7.57, "cleanText": [["but", "this", "definition", "that", "congress", "put", "in", "provide", "as", "follow"]]}, {"text": "\"The term interstate or foreign commerce shall mean transportation from one state, territory, or the District of Columbia to another state. \"", "start": 1057.698, "stop": 1070.006, "duration": 12.31, "cleanText": [["the", "term", "interstate", "or", "foreign", "commerce", "shall", "mean", "transportation", "from", "one", "state", "territory", "or", "the", "district", "of", "columbia", "to", "another", "state"]]}, {"text": "et cetera.", "start": 1070.006, "stop": 1071.874, "duration": 1.87, "cleanText": [["et", "cetera"]]}, {"text": "Now, reading the statute as with that language in it, it would read,", "start": 1071.874, "stop": 1079.397, "duration": 7.52, "cleanText": [["now", "read", "the", "statute", "as", "with", "that", "language", "in", "it", "it", "would", "read"]]}, {"text": "\"Whoever with unlawful or fraudulent intent transports from one state to another a falsely made, forged, altered, or counterfeited security. \"", "start": 1079.397, "stop": 1093.204, "duration": 13.81, "cleanText": [["whoever", "with", "unlawful", "or", "fraudulent", "intent", "transport", "from", "one", "state", "to", "another", "a", "falsely", "make", "forge", "alter", "or", "counterfeit", "security"]]}, {"text": "which clearly sets up our position in this case.", "start": 1093.204, "stop": 1097.941, "duration": 4.74, "cleanText": [["which", "clearly", "set", "up", "our", "position", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "But that is quite a narrower reading than the actual language of the statute itself.", "start": 1097.941, "stop": 1101.81, "duration": 3.87, "cleanText": [["but", "that", "be", "quite", "a", "narrow", "reading", "than", "the", "actual", "language", "of", "the", "statute", "itself"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, yes, but if we are looking to divine the will of Congress at the time the Act was passed, I think you have to look at the definition that they used.", "start": 1101.81, "stop": 1113.451, "duration": 11.64, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "yes", "but", "if", "we", "be", "look", "to", "divine", "the", "will", "of", "congress", "at", "the", "time", "the", "act", "be", "pass", "i", "think", "you", "have", "to", "look", "at", "the", "definition", "that", "they", "use"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, why don't we first look to the statute?", "start": 1113.451, "stop": 1115.32, "duration": 1.87, "cleanText": [["well", "why", "do", "not", "we", "first", "look", "to", "the", "statute"]]}, {"text": "The language of 2314 itself?", "start": 1115.32, "stop": 1119.689, "duration": 4.37, "cleanText": [["the", "language", "of", "itself"]]}, {"text": "Which says,", "start": 1119.689, "stop": 1120.105, "duration": 0.42, "cleanText": [["which", "say"]]}, {"text": "\"Whoever with unlawful or fraudulent intent transports in interstate commerce any forged security. \"", "start": 1120.105, "stop": 1125.473, "duration": 5.37, "cleanText": [["whoever", "with", "unlawful", "or", "fraudulent", "intent", "transport", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "any", "forge", "security"]]}, {"text": "I don't think it is unreasonable to say that when they talk about transporting in interstate commerce, they referred to the entire journey, and if the forgery takes place at any time during that journey, the violation is complete.", "start": 1125.473, "stop": 1141.518, "duration": 16.05, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "think", "it", "be", "unreasonable", "to", "say", "that", "when", "they", "talk", "about", "transporting", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "they", "refer", "to", "the", "entire", "journey", "and", "if", "the", "forgery", "take", "place", "at", "any", "time", "during", "that", "journey", "the", "violation", "be", "complete"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, if that were the case, then that would swallow up 2315.", "start": 1141.518, "stop": 1146.636, "duration": 5.12, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "if", "that", "we", "be", "the", "case", "then", "that", "would", "swallow", "up"]]}, {"text": "You would never need 2315.", "start": 1146.636, "stop": 1148.422, "duration": 1.79, "cleanText": [["you", "would", "never", "need"]]}, {"text": "There would be no reason to have 2315.", "start": 1148.422, "stop": 1152.457, "duration": 4.04, "cleanText": [["there", "would", "be", "no", "reason", "to", "have"]]}, {"text": "And that is our point.", "start": 1152.457, "stop": 1154.659, "duration": 2.2, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "our", "point"]]}, {"text": "When you read it with \"from state to state\" it means that the document has to be in a forged condition prior to its transportation.", "start": 1154.659, "stop": 1163.514, "duration": 8.85, "cleanText": [["when", "you", "read", "it", "with", "from", "state", "to", "state", "it", "mean", "that", "the", "document", "have", "to", "be", "in", "a", "forged", "condition", "prior", "to", "its", "transportation"]]}, {"text": "Now, I will admit that the definition that I told you that Congress had implanted into the Act was taken out by the general code revisions in 1949, and was replaced by Section 10, but the drafters of those sections, and when they revised 2314 and 2315, noted that there was no change in substance, there was merely changes in minor phraseology, and therefore that leaves us with the same intent and the same expression of Congress's will.", "start": 1163.514, "stop": 1203.14, "duration": 39.63, "cleanText": [["now", "i", "will", "admit", "that", "the", "definition", "that", "i", "tell", "you", "that", "congress", "have", "implant", "into", "the", "act", "be", "take", "out", "by", "the", "general", "code", "revision", "in", "and", "be", "replace", "by", "section", "but", "the", "drafter", "of", "those", "section", "and", "when", "they", "revise", "and", "note", "that", "there", "be", "no", "change", "in", "substance", "there", "be", "merely", "change", "in", "minor", "phraseology", "and", "therefore", "that", "leave", "us", "with", "the", "same", "intent", "and", "the", "same", "expression", "of", "congress", "s", "will"]]}, {"text": "Furthermore, the Act has been amended several times to provide for the same prohibitions with tax stamps and forged countersignatures on traveler's checks, and in several other ways.", "start": 1203.14, "stop": 1218.482, "duration": 15.34, "cleanText": [["furthermore", "the", "act", "have", "be", "amend", "several", "time", "to", "provide", "for", "the", "same", "prohibition", "with", "tax", "stamp", "and", "forge", "countersignature", "on", "traveler", "s", "check", "and", "in", "several", "other", "way"]]}, {"text": "Nobody has ever bothered to change the definition or make it clearer or anything, and furthermore, when they put in... when Congress wants to show in 2314 what it is that they want to cover, in the third paragraph it reads... I am sorry, in the second paragraph,", "start": 1218.482, "stop": 1242.015, "duration": 23.53, "cleanText": [["nobody", "have", "ever", "bother", "to", "change", "the", "definition", "or", "make", "it", "clear", "or", "anything", "and", "furthermore", "when", "they", "put", "in", "when", "congress", "want", "to", "show", "in", "what", "it", "be", "that", "they", "want", "to", "cover", "in", "the", "third", "paragraph", "it", "read", "i", "be", "sorry", "in", "the", "second", "paragraph"]]}, {"text": "\"Whoever having devised or intended to devise any scheme or artifice to defraud or the obtaining money or property by means of false or fraudulent pretenses. \"", "start": 1242.015, "stop": 1253.655, "duration": 11.64, "cleanText": [["whoever", "have", "devise", "or", "intend", "to", "devise", "any", "scheme", "or", "artifice", "to", "defraud", "or", "the", "obtain", "money", "or", "property", "by", "mean", "of", "false", "or", "fraudulent", "pretenses"]]}, {"text": "They can speak in language of intent now and intent later, not in the third paragraph of this statute.", "start": 1253.655, "stop": 1261.976, "duration": 8.32, "cleanText": [["they", "can", "speak", "in", "language", "of", "intent", "now", "and", "intent", "later", "not", "in", "the", "third", "paragraph", "of", "this", "statute"]]}, {"text": "It is to my mind clear and unambiguous, and three circuits have so found, and that basically is our position.", "start": 1261.976, "stop": 1273.534, "duration": 11.56, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "to", "my", "mind", "clear", "and", "unambiguous", "and", "three", "circuit", "have", "so", "find", "and", "that", "basically", "be", "our", "position"]]}, {"text": "We would cite the Court, of course, to your case of United States versus Barrett, where Justice Blackmun said that where Congress has utilized verb tenses and subrogated them throughout the entire Act, and seemed to know what they were doing when they did it, then we will give full weight and be influenced by that to a great degree, and in this case I think that is exactly what we have.", "start": 1273.534, "stop": 1307.707, "duration": 34.17, "cleanText": [["we", "would", "cite", "the", "court", "of", "course", "to", "your", "case", "of", "united", "state", "versus", "barrett", "where", "justice", "blackmun", "say", "that", "where", "congress", "have", "utilize", "verb", "tense", "and", "subrogate", "them", "throughout", "the", "entire", "act", "and", "seem", "to", "know", "what", "they", "we", "be", "do", "when", "they", "do", "it", "then", "we", "will", "give", "full", "weight", "and", "be", "influence", "by", "that", "to", "a", "great", "degree", "and", "in", "this", "case", "i", "think", "that", "be", "exactly", "what", "we", "have"]]}, {"text": "If there is an ambiguity, then that should be resolved in favor of the petitioner, because Congress's will has certainly not been unerringly clear in this situation.", "start": 1307.707, "stop": 1323.3, "duration": 15.59, "cleanText": [["if", "there", "be", "an", "ambiguity", "then", "that", "should", "be", "resolve", "in", "favor", "of", "the", "petitioner", "because", "congress", "s", "will", "have", "certainly", "not", "be", "unerringly", "clear", "in", "this", "situation"]]}, {"text": "Otherwise, we wouldn't have these three circuits' courts of appeals, and one was an en banc decision reading this statute so clearly.", "start": 1323.3, "stop": 1334.357, "duration": 11.06, "cleanText": [["otherwise", "we", "would", "not", "have", "these", "three", "circuit", "court", "of", "appeal", "and", "one", "be", "an", "en", "banc", "decision", "read", "this", "statute", "so", "clearly"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Would you say that he knew that that check had been stolen when he--", "start": 1334.357, "stop": 1340.011, "duration": 5.65, "cleanText": [["would", "you", "say", "that", "he", "know", "that", "that", "check", "have", "be", "steal", "when", "he"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Your Honor, there is no evidence that the petitioner--", "start": 1340.011, "stop": 1345.748, "duration": 5.74, "cleanText": [["your", "honor", "there", "be", "no", "evidence", "that", "the", "petitioner"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "--There isn't?", "start": 1345.748, "stop": 1346.815, "duration": 1.07, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--engaging in the theft.", "start": 1346.815, "stop": 1348.7, "duration": 1.88, "cleanText": [["engage", "in", "the", "theft"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, what about the old inference that can be drawn from possession of recently stolen property?", "start": 1348.7, "stop": 1357.723, "duration": 9.02, "cleanText": [["well", "what", "about", "the", "old", "inference", "that", "can", "be", "draw", "from", "possession", "of", "recently", "steal", "property"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor, he could do that, but remember, he is not charged with the theft.", "start": 1357.723, "stop": 1362.442, "duration": 4.72, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor", "he", "could", "do", "that", "but", "remember", "he", "be", "not", "charge", "with", "the", "theft"]]}, {"text": "What we are dealing with here is--", "start": 1362.442, "stop": 1364.21, "duration": 1.77, "cleanText": [["what", "we", "be", "deal", "with", "here", "be"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "No, I am just reading the statute.", "start": 1364.21, "stop": 1366.596, "duration": 2.39, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "be", "just", "read", "the", "statute"]]}, {"text": "Whoever transports in interstate commerce, and so forth, any securities, and so forth, knowing the same to have been stolen, converted, or taken by fraud.", "start": 1366.596, "stop": 1377.386, "duration": 10.79, "cleanText": [["whoever", "transport", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "and", "so", "forth", "any", "security", "and", "so", "forth", "know", "the", "same", "to", "have", "be", "steal", "convert", "or", "take", "by", "fraud"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--You are talking about the first paragraph, Your Honor?", "start": 1377.386, "stop": 1380.255, "duration": 2.87, "cleanText": [["you", "be", "talk", "about", "the", "first", "paragraph", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Of 2314.", "start": 1380.255, "stop": 1381.655, "duration": 1.4, "cleanText": [["of"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, the first paragraph.", "start": 1381.655, "stop": 1382.855, "duration": 1.2, "cleanText": [["yes", "the", "first", "paragraph"]]}, {"text": "That has the $5,000 limit.", "start": 1382.855, "stop": 1384.89, "duration": 2.04, "cleanText": [["that", "have", "the", "limit"]]}, {"text": "He couldn't have been charged... he wasn't charged with that.", "start": 1384.89, "stop": 1389.694, "duration": 4.8, "cleanText": [["he", "could", "not", "have", "be", "charge", "he", "be", "not", "charge", "with", "that"]]}, {"text": "You see, the government was very specific in this case.", "start": 1389.694, "stop": 1392.396, "duration": 2.7, "cleanText": [["you", "see", "the", "government", "be", "very", "specific", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "At the trial, the government attorney announced to the court clearly what we have here and what I am charging this man with is a violation of the third paragraph of 2314.", "start": 1392.396, "stop": 1405.037, "duration": 12.64, "cleanText": [["at", "the", "trial", "the", "government", "attorney", "announce", "to", "the", "court", "clearly", "what", "we", "have", "here", "and", "what", "i", "be", "charge", "this", "man", "with", "be", "a", "violation", "of", "the", "third", "paragraph", "of"]]}, {"text": "There was never any question that he was not being charged with anything else... or that he was being charged with anything else other than that one paragraph.", "start": 1405.037, "stop": 1416.726, "duration": 11.69, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "never", "any", "question", "that", "he", "be", "not", "be", "charge", "with", "anything", "else", "or", "that", "he", "be", "be", "charge", "with", "anything", "else", "other", "than", "that", "one", "paragraph"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, your brief... I am reading from Page 3, going over to 4, recites that he was charged of doing this in violation of 2314.", "start": 1416.726, "stop": 1429.818, "duration": 13.09, "cleanText": [["well", "your", "brief", "i", "be", "read", "from", "page", "go", "over", "to", "recite", "that", "he", "be", "charge", "of", "do", "this", "in", "violation", "of"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "It is a shorthand way of saying it, Your Honor, the paragraph that is involved, because we clearly pointed out the paragraph, Your Honor, and the whole record is replete with the fact that the judge and the U. S. Attorney and the attorney and the defendant all realized exactly what he was being charged with, and that is what went on in the court of appeals also.", "start": 1429.818, "stop": 1455.803, "duration": 25.99, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "a", "shorthand", "way", "of", "say", "it", "your", "honor", "the", "paragraph", "that", "be", "involve", "because", "we", "clearly", "point", "out", "the", "paragraph", "your", "honor", "and", "the", "whole", "record", "be", "replete", "with", "the", "fact", "that", "the", "judge", "and", "the", "you"], ["s", "attorney", "and", "the", "attorney", "and", "the", "defendant", "all", "realize", "exactly", "what", "he", "be", "be", "charge", "with", "and", "that", "be", "what", "go", "on", "in", "the", "court", "of", "appeal", "also"]]}, {"text": "There is no question about the specificity of the charges in this case.", "start": 1455.803, "stop": 1459.922, "duration": 4.12, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "no", "question", "about", "the", "specificity", "of", "the", "charge", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Very well.", "start": 1459.922, "stop": 1461.957, "duration": 2.04, "cleanText": [["very", "well"]]}, {"text": "Mr. Phillips?", "start": 1461.957, "stop": 1466.659, "duration": 4.7, "cleanText": [["mr", "phillips"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, Mr. Chief Justice, and may it please the Court, this case is here on a writ of certiorari limited to the issue of the proper scope of the interstate commerce requirement in Section 2314 of Title XVIII of the United States Code.", "start": 1466.659, "stop": 1479.751, "duration": 13.09, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "mr", "chief", "justice", "and", "may", "it", "please", "the", "court", "this", "case", "be", "here", "on", "a", "writ", "of", "certiorari", "limit", "to", "the", "issue", "of", "the", "proper", "scope", "of", "the", "interstate", "commerce", "requirement", "in", "section", "of", "title", "xviii", "of", "the", "united", "state", "code"]]}, {"text": "Specifically, the issue is whether in a prosecution for transporting a forged security in interstate commerce, the government must prove that the security in question was forged prior to the time the security reached its destination state or whether instead the government need only prove that a security was transported between one or more... between two or more states, and that prior to the time it reached its ultimate destination, that security was in a forged condition.", "start": 1479.751, "stop": 1508.437, "duration": 28.69, "cleanText": [["specifically", "the", "issue", "be", "whether", "in", "a", "prosecution", "for", "transport", "a", "forged", "security", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "the", "government", "must", "prove", "that", "the", "security", "in", "question", "be", "forge", "prior", "to", "the", "time", "the", "security", "reach", "its", "destination", "state", "or", "whether", "instead", "the", "government", "need", "only", "prove", "that", "a", "security", "be", "transport", "between", "one", "or", "more", "between", "two", "or", "more", "state", "and", "that", "prior", "to", "the", "time", "it", "reach", "its", "ultimate", "destination", "that", "security", "be", "in", "a", "forged", "condition"]]}, {"text": "Petitioner has adequately stated the facts, and I think it is abundantly clear from those facts that what is at issue here is the transportation of a security from Ohio to Pennsylvania, and the only question that is open is when was the forgery, and there is essentially no evidence in the record as to when the actual signature was placed on the specific security.", "start": 1508.437, "stop": 1531.618, "duration": 23.18, "cleanText": [["petitioner", "have", "adequately", "state", "the", "fact", "and", "i", "think", "it", "be", "abundantly", "clear", "from", "those", "fact", "that", "what", "be", "at", "issue", "here", "be", "the", "transportation", "of", "a", "security", "from", "ohio", "to", "pennsylvania", "and", "the", "only", "question", "that", "be", "open", "be", "when", "be", "the", "forgery", "and", "there", "be", "essentially", "no", "evidence", "in", "the", "record", "as", "to", "when", "the", "actual", "signature", "be", "place", "on", "the", "specific", "security"]]}, {"text": "The district court instructed the jury that if you believe that the government has shown that the defendant transported the checks while they were in a forged condition within the state of Pennsylvania, the requirements of the law are satisfied if that transportation was part of interstate commerce.", "start": 1531.618, "stop": 1548.396, "duration": 16.78, "cleanText": [["the", "district", "court", "instruct", "the", "jury", "that", "if", "you", "believe", "that", "the", "government", "have", "show", "that", "the", "defendant", "transport", "the", "check", "while", "they", "we", "be", "in", "a", "forged", "condition", "within", "the", "state", "of", "pennsylvania", "the", "requirement", "of", "the", "law", "be", "satisfy", "if", "that", "transportation", "be", "part", "of", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "That was the instruction offered by the government, and it was over the objection of the petitioner.", "start": 1548.396, "stop": 1554.466, "duration": 6.07, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "the", "instruction", "offer", "by", "the", "government", "and", "it", "be", "over", "the", "objection", "of", "the", "petitioner"]]}, {"text": "The jury convicted on that instruction, and so there is no dispute that what we are talking about here is a conviction on the basis of the third paragraph of Section 2314.", "start": 1554.466, "stop": 1563.672, "duration": 9.21, "cleanText": [["the", "jury", "convict", "on", "that", "instruction", "and", "so", "there", "be", "no", "dispute", "that", "what", "we", "be", "talk", "about", "here", "be", "a", "conviction", "on", "the", "basis", "of", "the", "third", "paragraph", "of", "section"]]}, {"text": "The Third Circuit affirmed the conviction on Section 2314, and it did so en banc.", "start": 1563.672, "stop": 1571.511, "duration": 7.84, "cleanText": [["the", "third", "circuit", "affirm", "the", "conviction", "on", "section", "and", "it", "do", "so", "en", "banc"]]}, {"text": "Nine of the ten judges on the Third Circuit adopted the theory of the government in this case.", "start": 1571.511, "stop": 1576.13, "duration": 4.62, "cleanText": [["nine", "of", "the", "ten", "judge", "on", "the", "third", "circuit", "adopt", "the", "theory", "of", "the", "government", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "The concurring opinion by Judge Adams... or, excuse me, the dissenting and concurring opinion by Judge Adams dissented solely from the reversal of the conviction on the Dyer Act count.", "start": 1576.13, "stop": 1589.64, "duration": 13.51, "cleanText": [["the", "concur", "opinion", "by", "judge", "adam", "or", "excuse", "me", "the", "dissenting", "and", "concur", "opinion", "by", "judge", "adam", "dissent", "solely", "from", "the", "reversal", "of", "the", "conviction", "on", "the", "dyer", "act", "count"]]}, {"text": "Judge Garth in his dissenting opinion agreed with the theory of the government's case but disagreed with the proof showing that the security in question had been transported from Ohio to Pennsylvania.", "start": 1589.64, "stop": 1602.899, "duration": 13.26, "cleanText": [["judge", "garth", "in", "his", "dissenting", "opinion", "agree", "with", "the", "theory", "of", "the", "government", "s", "case", "but", "disagreed", "with", "the", "proof", "show", "that", "the", "security", "in", "question", "have", "be", "transport", "from", "ohio", "to", "pennsylvania"]]}, {"text": "And finally, only Judge Higginbotham dissented basically relying on the decisions of the three other courts of appeals that have held similar to the way that petitioner argues in this case.", "start": 1602.899, "stop": 1613.188, "duration": 10.29, "cleanText": [["and", "finally", "only", "judge", "higginbotham", "dissent", "basically", "rely", "on", "the", "decision", "of", "the", "three", "other", "court", "of", "appeal", "that", "have", "hold", "similar", "to", "the", "way", "that", "petitioner", "argue", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "Frankly, from the government's perspective it is fairly unusual for three courts of appeals to interpret the same provision in a way that we believe is so fundamentally wrong, and so it seems appropriate to begin our analysis by attempting to explain how three courts of appeals have gone off on that ground.", "start": 1613.188, "stop": 1629.265, "duration": 16.08, "cleanText": [["frankly", "from", "the", "government", "s", "perspective", "it", "be", "fairly", "unusual", "for", "three", "court", "of", "appeal", "to", "interpret", "the", "same", "provision", "in", "a", "way", "that", "we", "believe", "be", "so", "fundamentally", "wrong", "and", "so", "it", "seem", "appropriate", "to", "begin", "our", "analysis", "by", "attempt", "to", "explain", "how", "three", "court", "of", "appeal", "have", "go", "off", "on", "that", "ground"]]}, {"text": "Petitioner in his submission has relied heavily on the presence of those decisions.", "start": 1629.265, "stop": 1635.668, "duration": 6.4, "cleanText": [["petitioner", "in", "his", "submission", "have", "rely", "heavily", "on", "the", "presence", "of", "those", "decision"]]}, {"text": "The source of the law in this area begins in 1961 in United States versus Castle, a case in which the fortuity of events, which was primarily a confession on the part of a defendant that he had forged documents in Maryland and then transported those securities into Texas, was relied upon by the court quite properly as stating each of the elements of a conviction under Paragraph 3 of Section 2314.", "start": 1635.668, "stop": 1662.485, "duration": 26.82, "cleanText": [["the", "source", "of", "the", "law", "in", "this", "area", "begin", "in", "in", "united", "state", "versus", "castle", "a", "case", "in", "which", "the", "fortuity", "of", "event", "which", "be", "primarily", "a", "confession", "on", "the", "part", "of", "a", "defendant", "that", "he", "have", "forge", "document", "in", "maryland", "and", "then", "transport", "those", "security", "into", "texas", "be", "rely", "upon", "by", "the", "court", "quite", "properly", "as", "state", "each", "of", "the", "element", "of", "a", "conviction", "under", "paragraph", "of", "section"]]}, {"text": "That factual oddity was suddenly transformed into an element of the defense indicta, frankly, by the same court of appeals, the Fifth Circuit, in United States versus Owens.", "start": 1662.485, "stop": 1674.126, "duration": 11.64, "cleanText": [["that", "factual", "oddity", "be", "suddenly", "transform", "into", "an", "element", "of", "the", "defense", "indicta", "frankly", "by", "the", "same", "court", "of", "appeal", "the", "fifth", "circuit", "in", "united", "state", "versus", "owen"]]}, {"text": "In Owens, the evidence simply proved that the defendant had attempted to cash securities that could be linked back eventually to New Jersey, the securities having been cashed in Louisiana.", "start": 1674.126, "stop": 1686.684, "duration": 12.56, "cleanText": [["in", "owen", "the", "evidence", "simply", "prove", "that", "the", "defendant", "have", "attempt", "to", "cash", "security", "that", "could", "be", "link", "back", "eventually", "to", "new", "jersey", "the", "security", "have", "be", "cash", "in", "louisiana"]]}, {"text": "Unfortunately for the government, there was no proof really as to how the securities had reached Louisiana, nor even how the defendant in that case had come by... had obtained those securities, and therefore there was no real proof of transportation.", "start": 1686.684, "stop": 1702.793, "duration": 16.11, "cleanText": [["unfortunately", "for", "the", "government", "there", "be", "no", "proof", "really", "as", "to", "how", "the", "security", "have", "reach", "louisiana", "nor", "even", "how", "the", "defendant", "in", "that", "case", "have", "come", "by", "have", "obtain", "those", "security", "and", "therefore", "there", "be", "no", "real", "proof", "of", "transportation"]]}, {"text": "The court threw out the conviction on the basis that there was inadequate evidence.", "start": 1702.793, "stop": 1706.245, "duration": 3.45, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "throw", "out", "the", "conviction", "on", "the", "basis", "that", "there", "be", "inadequate", "evidence"]]}, {"text": "Unfortunately indeed for the government, in doing so, the court also said that the important element that was missing was the failure to prove the fraud at the time of the interstate passage, moving away from the interstate commerce language, which is the linchpin of the government's position in this case.", "start": 1706.245, "stop": 1725.642, "duration": 19.4, "cleanText": [["unfortunately", "indeed", "for", "the", "government", "in", "do", "so", "the", "court", "also", "say", "that", "the", "important", "element", "that", "be", "miss", "be", "the", "failure", "to", "prove", "the", "fraud", "at", "the", "time", "of", "the", "interstate", "passage", "move", "away", "from", "the", "interstate", "commerce", "language", "which", "be", "the", "linchpin", "of", "the", "government", "s", "position", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "That language in the opinion of the Fifth Circuit was used by the Eighth Circuit in a subsequent decision involving a Section 2255 review of a guilty plea under Section 2314 where the defendant in that case had plead to having transported securities from one state to another.", "start": 1725.642, "stop": 1744.519, "duration": 18.88, "cleanText": [["that", "language", "in", "the", "opinion", "of", "the", "fifth", "circuit", "be", "use", "by", "the", "eighth", "circuit", "in", "a", "subsequent", "decision", "involve", "a", "section", "review", "of", "a", "guilty", "plea", "under", "section", "where", "the", "defendant", "in", "that", "case", "have", "plead", "to", "have", "transport", "security", "from", "one", "state", "to", "another"]]}, {"text": "The court found that there had been no proof that those checks had been forged in the state of origin and then transported, thereby truly effectuating the final development of the rule that petitioner seeks to have adopted by this court.", "start": 1744.519, "stop": 1763.331, "duration": 18.81, "cleanText": [["the", "court", "find", "that", "there", "have", "be", "no", "proof", "that", "those", "check", "have", "be", "forge", "in", "the", "state", "of", "origin", "and", "then", "transport", "thereby", "truly", "effectuate", "the", "final", "development", "of", "the", "rule", "that", "petitioner", "seek", "to", "have", "adopt", "by", "this", "court"]]}, {"text": "That decision then was followed in turn by the Tenth Circuit en banc.", "start": 1763.331, "stop": 1766.949, "duration": 3.62, "cleanText": [["that", "decision", "then", "be", "follow", "in", "turn", "by", "the", "tenth", "circuit", "en", "banc"]]}, {"text": "The decision in Sparrow, I submit, reflects nothing more than the desire of the Tenth Circuit to avoid a conflict among the circuits.", "start": 1766.949, "stop": 1774.603, "duration": 7.65, "cleanText": [["the", "decision", "in", "sparrow", "i", "submit", "reflect", "nothing", "more", "than", "the", "desire", "of", "the", "tenth", "circuit", "to", "avoid", "a", "conflict", "among", "the", "circuit"]]}, {"text": "It essentially recites the prior decisions in this area and does little more than cite the rule of Lenity as a basis for its ultimate decision.", "start": 1774.603, "stop": 1781.808, "duration": 7.2, "cleanText": [["it", "essentially", "recite", "the", "prior", "decision", "in", "this", "area", "and", "do", "little", "more", "than", "cite", "the", "rule", "of", "lenity", "as", "a", "basis", "for", "its", "ultimate", "decision"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Phillips, suppose a check is stolen in Pittsburgh and the check stays in Pennsylvania all the time but it is stolen by somebody from Cleveland, and he leaves the check in Pennsylvania with his colleagues and goes back to Cleveland, and then he goes to... makes a trip to Pittsburgh, picks up the check, and goes to Philadelphia, forges it in Philadelphia, and does whatever he did with it here.", "start": 1781.808, "stop": 1814.864, "duration": 33.06, "cleanText": [["mr", "phillips", "suppose", "a", "check", "be", "steal", "in", "pittsburgh", "and", "the", "check", "stay", "in", "pennsylvania", "all", "the", "time", "but", "it", "be", "steal", "by", "somebody", "from", "cleveland", "and", "he", "leave", "the", "check", "in", "pennsylvania", "with", "his", "colleague", "and", "go", "back", "to", "cleveland", "and", "then", "he", "go", "to", "make", "a", "trip", "to", "pittsburgh", "pick", "up", "the", "check", "and", "go", "to", "philadelphia", "forge", "it", "in", "philadelphia", "and", "do", "whatever", "he", "do", "with", "it", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it is difficult to know exactly, because the key to this is going to be whether or not--", "start": 1814.864, "stop": 1818.482, "duration": 3.62, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "be", "difficult", "to", "know", "exactly", "because", "the", "key", "to", "this", "be", "go", "to", "be", "whether", "or", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I would think if you mean literally what your submission is, that there is an interstate movement from Cleveland to Philadelphia.", "start": 1818.482, "stop": 1825.404, "duration": 6.92, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "would", "think", "if", "you", "mean", "literally", "what", "your", "submission", "be", "that", "there", "be", "an", "interstate", "movement", "from", "cleveland", "to", "philadelphia"]]}, {"text": "It doesn't make any difference whether the check itself crosses a state line or not.", "start": 1825.404, "stop": 1829.023, "duration": 3.62, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "make", "any", "difference", "whether", "the", "check", "itself", "cross", "a", "state", "line", "or", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, no, the check itself has to cross the state line as--", "start": 1829.023, "stop": 1833.308, "duration": 4.29, "cleanText": [["well", "no", "the", "check", "itself", "have", "to", "cross", "the", "state", "line", "as"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why?", "start": 1833.308, "stop": 1834.558, "duration": 1.25, "cleanText": [["why"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, at some point, it would be difficult--", "start": 1834.558, "stop": 1837.426, "duration": 2.87, "cleanText": [["well", "at", "some", "point", "it", "would", "be", "difficult"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "There is interstate commerce.", "start": 1837.426, "stop": 1839.212, "duration": 1.79, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "There is movement in interstate commerce.", "start": 1839.212, "stop": 1840.928, "duration": 1.72, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "movement", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Of the defendant.", "start": 1840.928, "stop": 1841.995, "duration": 1.07, "cleanText": [["of", "the", "defendant"]]}, {"text": "We are not submitting that there doesn't have to be some movement of the forged security.", "start": 1841.995, "stop": 1845.782, "duration": 3.79, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "not", "submit", "that", "there", "do", "not", "have", "to", "be", "some", "movement", "of", "the", "forged", "security"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I know, but the check is being transported in interstate commerce.", "start": 1845.782, "stop": 1847.949, "duration": 2.17, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "know", "but", "the", "check", "be", "be", "transport", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it may be that it is in interstate commerce.", "start": 1847.949, "stop": 1850.501, "duration": 2.55, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "may", "be", "that", "it", "be", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "The question... there would be essentially a question for the jury to decide whether or not it ever became in interstate commerce, and it may well be on the facts--", "start": 1850.501, "stop": 1859.106, "duration": 8.61, "cleanText": [["the", "question", "there", "would", "be", "essentially", "a", "question", "for", "the", "jury", "to", "decide", "whether", "or", "not", "it", "ever", "become", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "and", "it", "may", "well", "be", "on", "the", "fact"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, there is no doubt about it, the fellow drives from Cleveland to Pittsburgh, picks up the check, and goes on to Philadelphia, one movement.", "start": 1859.106, "stop": 1867.612, "duration": 8.51, "cleanText": [["well", "there", "be", "no", "doubt", "about", "it", "the", "fellow", "drive", "from", "cleveland", "to", "pittsburgh", "pick", "up", "the", "check", "and", "go", "on", "to", "philadelphia", "one", "movement"]]}, {"text": "The check is moving in interstate commerce, just as surely as if the check was moved from Cleveland to Pittsburgh.", "start": 1867.612, "stop": 1878.603, "duration": 10.99, "cleanText": [["the", "check", "be", "move", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "just", "as", "surely", "as", "if", "the", "check", "be", "move", "from", "cleveland", "to", "pittsburgh"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--It may be true, and I am not... if a jury were to convict on that theory, we would be here defending that conviction.", "start": 1878.603, "stop": 1885.241, "duration": 6.64, "cleanText": [["it", "may", "be", "true", "and", "i", "be", "not", "if", "a", "jury", "we", "be", "to", "convict", "on", "that", "theory", "we", "would", "be", "here", "defend", "that", "conviction"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "The jury... if the court instructed that you may find that the statute is satisfied if the check Just moves from Pittsburgh to Philadelphia, would you object to that or not?", "start": 1885.241, "stop": 1900.333, "duration": 15.09, "cleanText": [["the", "jury", "if", "the", "court", "instruct", "that", "you", "may", "find", "that", "the", "statute", "be", "satisfied", "if", "the", "check", "just", "move", "from", "pittsburgh", "to", "philadelphia", "would", "you", "object", "to", "that", "or", "not"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I can imagine that there... it would generally not be the case that that would ever have become in interstate commerce, because the check has never begun to move in interstate commerce.", "start": 1900.333, "stop": 1907.439, "duration": 7.11, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "can", "imagine", "that", "there", "it", "would", "generally", "not", "be", "the", "case", "that", "that", "would", "ever", "have", "become", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "because", "the", "check", "have", "never", "begin", "to", "move", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "The only person who has moved--", "start": 1907.439, "stop": 1908.939, "duration": 1.5, "cleanText": [["the", "only", "person", "who", "have", "move"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, they begin moving in interstate commerce as soon as they picked it up.", "start": 1908.939, "stop": 1912.058, "duration": 3.12, "cleanText": [["well", "they", "begin", "move", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "as", "soon", "as", "they", "pick", "it", "up"]]}, {"text": "It became part of an interstate trip.", "start": 1912.058, "stop": 1914.676, "duration": 2.62, "cleanText": [["it", "become", "part", "of", "an", "interstate", "trip"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, I suppose that you might say that the defendant's movement from Cleveland to Pittsburgh was sufficient to create a movement in interstate commerce.", "start": 1914.676, "stop": 1921.78, "duration": 7.1, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "suppose", "that", "you", "might", "say", "that", "the", "defendant", "s", "movement", "from", "cleveland", "to", "pittsburgh", "be", "sufficient", "to", "create", "a", "movement", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "I am sure you would.", "start": 1921.78, "stop": 1922.513, "duration": 0.73, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "sure", "you", "would"]]}, {"text": "If that was part of his plan.", "start": 1922.513, "stop": 1924.032, "duration": 1.52, "cleanText": [["if", "that", "be", "part", "of", "his", "plan"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "If that was part of his plan.", "start": 1924.032, "stop": 1925.298, "duration": 1.27, "cleanText": [["if", "that", "be", "part", "of", "his", "plan"]]}, {"text": "But we would have to demonstrate that that is all a continuous movement, and certainly if that kind of movement, relying on an individual from Cleveland to take up the check and move it along, is designed in some way along... to avoid detection, then it even falls clearly within the intendment of what Congress wanted under Section 2314.", "start": 1925.298, "stop": 1943.343, "duration": 18.05, "cleanText": [["but", "we", "would", "have", "to", "demonstrate", "that", "that", "be", "all", "a", "continuous", "movement", "and", "certainly", "if", "that", "kind", "of", "movement", "rely", "on", "an", "individual", "from", "cleveland", "to", "take", "up", "the", "check", "and", "move", "it", "along", "be", "design", "in", "some", "way", "along", "to", "avoid", "detection", "then", "it", "even", "fall", "clearly", "within", "the", "intendment", "of", "what", "congress", "want", "under", "section"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Is there or is there not a requirement in the statute that the check ever cross a state line?", "start": 1943.343, "stop": 1948.48, "duration": 5.14, "cleanText": [["be", "there", "or", "be", "there", "not", "a", "requirement", "in", "the", "statute", "that", "the", "check", "ever", "cross", "a", "state", "line"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, certainly we need go no further than that in this case, obviously, because the check did go across the state line.", "start": 1948.48, "stop": 1953.884, "duration": 5.4, "cleanText": [["well", "certainly", "we", "need", "go", "no", "further", "than", "that", "in", "this", "case", "obviously", "because", "the", "check", "do", "go", "across", "the", "state", "line"]]}, {"text": "I would think it would be generally difficult to make out a case when the check doesn't move across state lines.", "start": 1953.884, "stop": 1959.788, "duration": 5.9, "cleanText": [["i", "would", "think", "it", "would", "be", "generally", "difficult", "to", "make", "out", "a", "case", "when", "the", "check", "do", "not", "move", "across", "state", "line"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Why would there be any difference?", "start": 1959.788, "stop": 1960.421, "duration": 0.63, "cleanText": [["why", "would", "there", "be", "any", "difference"]]}, {"text": "Suppose you have the same facts you have here, except as Justice White suggests, the theft was from Pittsburgh, but yet he lived in Ohio, and he called up from the Ohio Turnpike to Beaver Falls and said, I am on my way in, I am going to pick up the check in Pittsburgh and deliver it to you.", "start": 1960.421, "stop": 1973.715, "duration": 13.29, "cleanText": [["suppose", "you", "have", "the", "same", "fact", "you", "have", "here", "except", "as", "justice", "white", "suggests", "the", "theft", "be", "from", "pittsburgh", "but", "yet", "he", "live", "in", "ohio", "and", "he", "call", "up", "from", "the", "ohio", "turnpike", "to", "beaver", "fall", "and", "say", "i", "be", "on", "my", "way", "in", "i", "be", "go", "to", "pick", "up", "the", "check", "in", "pittsburgh", "and", "deliver", "it", "to", "you"]]}, {"text": "He did exactly that, but it was a forged check.", "start": 1973.715, "stop": 1975.765, "duration": 2.05, "cleanText": [["he", "do", "exactly", "that", "but", "it", "be", "a", "forged", "check"]]}, {"text": "Wasn't that exactly like this case?", "start": 1975.765, "stop": 1978.166, "duration": 2.4, "cleanText": [["be", "not", "that", "exactly", "like", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "Sure.", "start": 1978.166, "stop": 1979.266, "duration": 1.1, "cleanText": [["sure"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, and that was the basis, I suppose, for Judge Garth's concurring and dissenting opinion saying the evidence was insufficient because we couldn't prove that he hadn't just picked up the checks from--", "start": 1979.266, "stop": 1987.438, "duration": 8.17, "cleanText": [["well", "and", "that", "be", "the", "basis", "i", "suppose", "for", "judge", "garth", "s", "concurring", "and", "dissent", "opinion", "say", "the", "evidence", "be", "insufficient", "because", "we", "could", "not", "prove", "that", "he", "have", "not", "just", "pick", "up", "the", "check", "from"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "So under your theory it would be all right.", "start": 1987.438, "stop": 1989.188, "duration": 1.75, "cleanText": [["so", "under", "your", "theory", "it", "would", "be", "all", "right"]]}, {"text": "There is just as much basis for requiring the check to cross the line in a forged condition as there is to have the check cross the line at all.", "start": 1989.188, "stop": 1997.46, "duration": 8.27, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "just", "as", "much", "basis", "for", "require", "the", "check", "to", "cross", "the", "line", "in", "a", "forged", "condition", "as", "there", "be", "to", "have", "the", "check", "cross", "the", "line", "at", "all"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--No, I don't believe that that is so, Your Honor.", "start": 1997.46, "stop": 1999.912, "duration": 2.45, "cleanText": [["no", "i", "do", "not", "believe", "that", "that", "be", "so", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "It seems to me that all the statute says is that you must transport in interstate commerce.", "start": 1999.912, "stop": 2004.214, "duration": 4.3, "cleanText": [["it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "all", "the", "statute", "say", "be", "that", "you", "must", "transport", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "It is the check that must be in interstate commerce, not the defendant.", "start": 2004.214, "stop": 2007.233, "duration": 3.02, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "the", "check", "that", "must", "be", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "not", "the", "defendant"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, the check is, on your theory.", "start": 2007.233, "stop": 2008.185, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["well", "the", "check", "be", "on", "your", "theory"]]}, {"text": "You say there is a whole movement.", "start": 2008.185, "stop": 2009.785, "duration": 1.6, "cleanText": [["you", "say", "there", "be", "a", "whole", "movement"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, that's right, Your Honor.", "start": 2009.785, "stop": 2010.935, "duration": 1.15, "cleanText": [["yes", "that", "be", "right", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "A whole movement, and if the check is part of it at all, it is moved in interstate commerce.", "start": 2010.935, "stop": 2015.506, "duration": 4.57, "cleanText": [["a", "whole", "movement", "and", "if", "the", "check", "be", "part", "of", "it", "at", "all", "it", "be", "move", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "It doesn't have to cross the line.", "start": 2015.506, "stop": 2016.622, "duration": 1.12, "cleanText": [["it", "do", "not", "have", "to", "cross", "the", "line"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "It is transported in interstate commerce.", "start": 2016.622, "stop": 2017.458, "duration": 0.84, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "transport", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "But we are not saying, moving as in interstate commerce.", "start": 2017.458, "stop": 2020.992, "duration": 3.53, "cleanText": [["but", "we", "be", "not", "say", "move", "as", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "We are simply saying transported in interstate commerce.", "start": 2020.992, "stop": 2023.444, "duration": 2.45, "cleanText": [["we", "be", "simply", "say", "transport", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Phillips.", "start": 2023.444, "stop": 2024.394, "duration": 0.95, "cleanText": [["mr", "phillips"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 2024.394, "stop": 2025.294, "duration": 0.9, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Take two cases.", "start": 2025.294, "stop": 2026.479, "duration": 1.18, "cleanText": [["take", "two", "case"]]}, {"text": "One, that this Court says that you have to forge the check before you cross the state line, and you try a man, and he says, I forged it after I crossed the state line.", "start": 2026.479, "stop": 2040.037, "duration": 13.56, "cleanText": [["one", "that", "this", "court", "say", "that", "you", "have", "to", "forge", "the", "check", "before", "you", "cross", "the", "state", "line", "and", "you", "try", "a", "man", "and", "he", "say", "i", "forge", "it", "after", "i", "cross", "the", "state", "line"]]}, {"text": "Secondly, this Court says, you only can be guilty if you forge it after you cross the state line, and the man is brought in, and he says, I forged it before I crossed the state line.", "start": 2040.037, "stop": 2052.262, "duration": 12.23, "cleanText": [["secondly", "this", "court", "say", "you", "only", "can", "be", "guilty", "if", "you", "forge", "it", "after", "you", "cross", "the", "state", "line", "and", "the", "man", "be", "bring", "in", "and", "he", "say", "i", "forge", "it", "before", "i", "cross", "the", "state", "line"]]}, {"text": "Wouldn't both of them go free?", "start": 2052.262, "stop": 2053.845, "duration": 1.58, "cleanText": [["would", "not", "both", "of", "them", "go", "free"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "If the rule is as you state it--", "start": 2053.845, "stop": 2057.047, "duration": 3.2, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "rule", "be", "as", "you", "state", "it"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "If the rule is that way.", "start": 2057.047, "stop": 2057.83, "duration": 0.78, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "rule", "be", "that", "way"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, sir.", "start": 2057.83, "stop": 2058.249, "duration": 0.42, "cleanText": [["yes", "sir"]]}, {"text": "We would have some difficulty.", "start": 2058.249, "stop": 2060.049, "duration": 1.8, "cleanText": [["we", "would", "have", "some", "difficulty"]]}, {"text": "And I suppose that is why we take the position we do here, which is that we simply cannot prove when the defendant forges the check.", "start": 2060.049, "stop": 2066.653, "duration": 6.6, "cleanText": [["and", "i", "suppose", "that", "be", "why", "we", "take", "the", "position", "we", "do", "here", "which", "be", "that", "we", "simply", "can", "not", "prove", "when", "the", "defendant", "forge", "the", "check"]]}, {"text": "There are few events that are more a secret than the timing of a forgery, and that is why we think that in this situation we have proved out all that is required under the statute.", "start": 2066.653, "stop": 2077.043, "duration": 10.39, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "few", "event", "that", "be", "more", "a", "secret", "than", "the", "timing", "of", "a", "forgery", "and", "that", "be", "why", "we", "think", "that", "in", "this", "situation", "we", "have", "prove", "out", "all", "that", "be", "require", "under", "the", "statute"]]}, {"text": "As I suggest, it seems to me that the Fifth, Eighth, and Tenth Circuits, although they have in fact reached results contrary to the ones we assert in this case, supply petitioner with very little assistance in this case, because those decisions are not based on the sort of building blocks of statutory interpretation one would expect to be used, that is, the specific language used in the statute, the legislative history behind the statute, and the relationship of this provision to other comparable provisions in the code.", "start": 2077.043, "stop": 2103.445, "duration": 26.4, "cleanText": [["as", "i", "suggest", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "the", "fifth", "eighth", "and", "tenth", "circuit", "although", "they", "have", "in", "fact", "reach", "result", "contrary", "to", "the", "one", "we", "assert", "in", "this", "case", "supply", "petitioner", "with", "very", "little", "assistance", "in", "this", "case", "because", "those", "decision", "be", "not", "base", "on", "the", "sort", "of", "building", "block", "of", "statutory", "interpretation", "one", "would", "expect", "to", "be", "use", "that", "be", "the", "specific", "language", "use", "in", "the", "statute", "the", "legislative", "history", "behind", "the", "statute", "and", "the", "relationship", "of", "this", "provision", "to", "other", "comparable", "provision", "in", "the", "code"]]}, {"text": "We reject, I think quite easily, the argument of petitioner that there is a clear meaning to this statute that precludes this prosecution.", "start": 2103.445, "stop": 2112.717, "duration": 9.27, "cleanText": [["we", "reject", "i", "think", "quite", "easily", "the", "argument", "of", "petitioner", "that", "there", "be", "a", "clear", "meaning", "to", "this", "statute", "that", "preclude", "this", "prosecution"]]}, {"text": "Petitioner's clear meaning from the statute is derived solely from the notion that would only make sense in the context of this statute precluded the transportation across a state line of a security, but that is not what this statute requires.", "start": 2112.717, "stop": 2127.393, "duration": 14.68, "cleanText": [["petitioner", "s", "clear", "meaning", "from", "the", "statute", "be", "derive", "solely", "from", "the", "notion", "that", "would", "only", "make", "sense", "in", "the", "context", "of", "this", "statute", "preclude", "the", "transportation", "across", "a", "state", "line", "of", "a", "security", "but", "that", "be", "not", "what", "this", "statute", "require"]]}, {"text": "Instead, it forbids transportation in interstate commerce, and the only way to know what transportation in interstate commerce violates the statute can be decided by reference to the legislative intent.", "start": 2127.393, "stop": 2138.749, "duration": 11.36, "cleanText": [["instead", "it", "forbid", "transportation", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "and", "the", "only", "way", "to", "know", "what", "transportation", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "violate", "the", "statute", "can", "be", "decide", "by", "reference", "to", "the", "legislative", "intent"]]}, {"text": "We suggest that the statute is at least ambiguous enough to require us to look to what Congress intended.", "start": 2138.749, "stop": 2144.419, "duration": 5.67, "cleanText": [["we", "suggest", "that", "the", "statute", "be", "at", "least", "ambiguous", "enough", "to", "require", "us", "to", "look", "to", "what", "congress", "intend"]]}, {"text": "By doing that, it seems to us very clear that the interstate commerce requirement in the statute is designed to be a much broader concept than the idea of crossing a state line.", "start": 2144.419, "stop": 2154.525, "duration": 10.11, "cleanText": [["by", "do", "that", "it", "seem", "to", "us", "very", "clear", "that", "the", "interstate", "commerce", "requirement", "in", "the", "statute", "be", "design", "to", "be", "a", "much", "broad", "concept", "than", "the", "idea", "of", "cross", "a", "state", "line"]]}, {"text": "Congress knew in 1919, it knew in 1934, and it knew in 1939 how the phrase \"interstate commerce\" had been interpreted by this Court, and it relied on that broad concept that movement in interstate commerce as a basis and with the desire to stop that kind of movement in interstate commerce.", "start": 2154.525, "stop": 2174.403, "duration": 19.88, "cleanText": [["congress", "know", "in", "it", "know", "in", "and", "it", "know", "in", "how", "the", "phrase", "interstate", "commerce", "have", "be", "interpret", "by", "this", "court", "and", "it", "rely", "on", "that", "broad", "concept", "that", "movement", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "as", "a", "basis", "and", "with", "the", "desire", "to", "stop", "that", "kind", "of", "movement", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "So that the semantic argument, it seems to us, if anything, is quite clear in our favor.", "start": 2174.403, "stop": 2179.223, "duration": 4.82, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "the", "semantic", "argument", "it", "seem", "to", "us", "if", "anything", "be", "quite", "clear", "in", "our", "favor"]]}, {"text": "Moreover, our semantic argument is buttressed significantly by the policy of this Act, which is to crush frauds committed on interstate commerce by use of the forged securities, and that policy is fully implemented in a case like this where the petitioner has shown himself capable of running back and forth between the states of Ohio and Pennsylvania, making detection of his crime difficult, and making the... and if there were not a provision like this, making prosecution for his crime quite difficult.", "start": 2179.223, "stop": 2213.128, "duration": 33.91, "cleanText": [["moreover", "our", "semantic", "argument", "be", "buttress", "significantly", "by", "the", "policy", "of", "this", "act", "which", "be", "to", "crush", "frauds", "commit", "on", "interstate", "commerce", "by", "use", "of", "the", "forged", "security", "and", "that", "policy", "be", "fully", "implement", "in", "a", "case", "like", "this", "where", "the", "petitioner", "have", "show", "himself", "capable", "of", "run", "back", "and", "forth", "between", "the", "state", "of", "ohio", "and", "pennsylvania", "make", "detection", "of", "his", "crime", "difficult", "and", "make", "the", "and", "if", "there", "we", "be", "not", "a", "provision", "like", "this", "make", "prosecution", "for", "his", "crime", "quite", "difficult"]]}, {"text": "It seems to me that the--", "start": 2213.128, "stop": 2215.314, "duration": 2.19, "cleanText": [["it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "the"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. Phillips, what do you say about his argument that you just used the wrong statutory provision, that you should have indicted under 2315?", "start": 2215.314, "stop": 2221.4, "duration": 6.09, "cleanText": [["mr", "phillips", "what", "do", "you", "say", "about", "his", "argument", "that", "you", "just", "use", "the", "wrong", "statutory", "provision", "that", "you", "should", "have", "indict", "under"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, it may well be that petitioner has violated several statutes, but one that he clearly violated was Section 2314.", "start": 2221.4, "stop": 2228.656, "duration": 7.26, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "may", "well", "be", "that", "petitioner", "have", "violate", "several", "statute", "but", "one", "that", "he", "clearly", "violate", "be", "section"]]}, {"text": "I don't see any necessary problem.", "start": 2228.656, "stop": 2232.191, "duration": 3.53, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "see", "any", "necessary", "problem"]]}, {"text": "The point is, he carried this security across state lines and held it for a while and used it for various purposes.", "start": 2232.191, "stop": 2238.262, "duration": 6.07, "cleanText": [["the", "point", "be", "he", "carry", "this", "security", "across", "state", "line", "and", "hold", "it", "for", "a", "while", "and", "use", "it", "for", "various", "purpose"]]}, {"text": "I have no doubt that we could have prosecuted--", "start": 2238.262, "stop": 2239.845, "duration": 1.58, "cleanText": [["i", "have", "no", "doubt", "that", "we", "could", "have", "prosecute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "But we have just agreed he doesn't really have to carry it across state lines, I thought, in order to come within the statute--", "start": 2239.845, "stop": 2244.166, "duration": 4.32, "cleanText": [["but", "we", "have", "just", "agree", "he", "do", "not", "really", "have", "to", "carry", "it", "across", "state", "line", "i", "think", "in", "order", "to", "come", "within", "the", "statute"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Well, he doesn't have to, but--", "start": 2244.166, "stop": 2245.416, "duration": 1.25, "cleanText": [["well", "he", "do", "not", "have", "to", "but"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "--whereas... and that is even clearer... pardon me?", "start": 2245.416, "stop": 2246.649, "duration": 1.23, "cleanText": [["whereas", "and", "that", "be", "even", "clear", "pardon", "me"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--I am sorry.", "start": 2246.649, "stop": 2247.284, "duration": 0.64, "cleanText": [["i", "be", "sorry"]]}, {"text": "I didn't mean to interrupt you.", "start": 2247.284, "stop": 2247.984, "duration": 0.7, "cleanText": [["i", "do", "not", "mean", "to", "interrupt", "you"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I guess we agreed on that.", "start": 2247.984, "stop": 2250.236, "duration": 2.25, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "guess", "we", "agree", "on", "that"]]}, {"text": "That your position does not require that the security ever cross state lines, it merely requires that it be transported during a part of an interstate journey.", "start": 2250.236, "stop": 2258.574, "duration": 8.34, "cleanText": [["that", "your", "position", "do", "not", "require", "that", "the", "security", "ever", "cross", "state", "line", "it", "merely", "require", "that", "it", "be", "transport", "during", "a", "part", "of", "an", "interstate", "journey"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "In part of a... yes, sir, That's correct.", "start": 2258.574, "stop": 2260.257, "duration": 1.68, "cleanText": [["in", "part", "of", "a", "yes", "sir", "that", "be", "correct"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "So that you get a commuter, if he picks up the forgery check after he crosses the state line.", "start": 2260.257, "stop": 2264.376, "duration": 4.12, "cleanText": [["so", "that", "you", "get", "a", "commuter", "if", "he", "pick", "up", "the", "forgery", "check", "after", "he", "cross", "the", "state", "line"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "That's correct, as long as it is all part of a single transportation in interstate commerce.", "start": 2264.376, "stop": 2267.828, "duration": 3.45, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "correct", "as", "long", "as", "it", "be", "all", "part", "of", "a", "single", "transportation", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "But I am just wondering if there is much of a federal interest at stake here if there is another statutory provision that covers this precise--", "start": 2267.828, "stop": 2273.898, "duration": 6.07, "cleanText": [["but", "i", "be", "just", "wonder", "if", "there", "be", "much", "of", "a", "federal", "interest", "at", "stake", "here", "if", "there", "be", "another", "statutory", "provision", "that", "cover", "this", "precise"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, I don't think that there is another provision that covers this precise--", "start": 2273.898, "stop": 2277.517, "duration": 3.62, "cleanText": [["well", "i", "do", "not", "think", "that", "there", "be", "another", "provision", "that", "cover", "this", "precise"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Situation?", "start": 2277.517, "stop": 2278.734, "duration": 1.22, "cleanText": [["situation"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "--situation.", "start": 2278.734, "stop": 2279.386, "duration": 0.65, "cleanText": [["situation"]]}, {"text": "I mean, it seems to me that 2315, which is more concerned with receipt of these kinds of securities, covers a different activity.", "start": 2279.386, "stop": 2286.722, "duration": 7.34, "cleanText": [["i", "mean", "it", "seem", "to", "me", "that", "which", "be", "more", "concerned", "with", "receipt", "of", "these", "kind", "of", "security", "cover", "a", "different", "activity"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, it is receives, conceals, stores, barters, sells, or disposes of.", "start": 2286.722, "stop": 2290.157, "duration": 3.43, "cleanText": [["well", "it", "be", "receives", "conceals", "store", "barter", "sell", "or", "disposes", "of"]]}, {"text": "There is clearly--", "start": 2290.157, "stop": 2290.907, "duration": 0.75, "cleanText": [["there", "be", "clearly"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Carter G. Phillips", "textObjs": [{"text": "Sure, but those all involve additional activities that are regarded as inimical by Congress, so that it would seem to me the fact that he has done more than one thing certainly is no basis for denying the government the right to prosecute him on this basis.", "start": 2290.907, "stop": 2304.251, "duration": 13.34, "cleanText": [["sure", "but", "those", "all", "involve", "additional", "activity", "that", "be", "regard", "as", "inimical", "by", "congress", "so", "that", "it", "would", "seem", "to", "me", "the", "fact", "that", "he", "have", "do", "more", "than", "one", "thing", "certainly", "be", "no", "basis", "for", "deny", "the", "government", "the", "right", "to", "prosecute", "him", "on", "this", "basis"]]}, {"text": "It seems to me ultimately that the only basis that... the only argument petitioner really has in this case is the rule of Lenity, and as I think is fairly clear, the rule of Lenity is only a matter of statutory construction.", "start": 2304.251, "stop": 2317.594, "duration": 13.34, "cleanText": [["it", "seem", "to", "me", "ultimately", "that", "the", "only", "basis", "that", "the", "only", "argument", "petitioner", "really", "have", "in", "this", "case", "be", "the", "rule", "of", "lenity", "and", "as", "i", "think", "be", "fairly", "clear", "the", "rule", "of", "lenity", "be", "only", "a", "matter", "of", "statutory", "construction"]]}, {"text": "It is really a rule in many ways designed simply for separation of powers... interests.", "start": 2317.594, "stop": 2322.646, "duration": 5.05, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "really", "a", "rule", "in", "many", "way", "design", "simply", "for", "separation", "of", "power", "interest"]]}, {"text": "That is that we want to make sure that Congress declares what crimes exist and how they ought to be punished, and as I hope I have suggested already, Congress has spoken very broadly in this statute, and clearly to include this conduct as within the prohibition of the statute.", "start": 2322.646, "stop": 2339.174, "duration": 16.53, "cleanText": [["that", "be", "that", "we", "want", "to", "make", "sure", "that", "congress", "declare", "what", "crime", "exist", "and", "how", "they", "ought", "to", "be", "punish", "and", "as", "i", "hope", "i", "have", "suggest", "already", "congress", "have", "speak", "very", "broadly", "in", "this", "statute", "and", "clearly", "to", "include", "this", "conduct", "as", "within", "the", "prohibition", "of", "the", "statute"]]}, {"text": "If there are no further questions, Your Honors, I would ask you to affirm the judgment of the Third Circuit in this case.", "start": 2339.174, "stop": 2344.078, "duration": 4.9, "cleanText": [["if", "there", "be", "no", "further", "question", "your", "honor", "i", "would", "ask", "you", "to", "affirm", "the", "judgment", "of", "the", "third", "circuit", "in", "this", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. White, do you have anything further?", "start": 2344.078, "stop": 2348.78, "duration": 4.7, "cleanText": [["mr", "white", "do", "you", "have", "anything", "far"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes, Your Honor.", "start": 2348.78, "stop": 2350.398, "duration": 1.62, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor"]]}, {"text": "Again, the government has not paid any attention to the fact that when this Act was passed, Congress put a definition into it, and did not rely on the broad interpretation of interstate commerce that he would suggest upon which they relied.", "start": 2350.398, "stop": 2366.825, "duration": 16.43, "cleanText": [["again", "the", "government", "have", "not", "pay", "any", "attention", "to", "the", "fact", "that", "when", "this", "act", "be", "pass", "congress", "put", "a", "definition", "into", "it", "and", "do", "not", "rely", "on", "the", "broad", "interpretation", "of", "interstate", "commerce", "that", "he", "would", "suggest", "upon", "which", "they", "rely"]]}, {"text": "Furthermore, it isn't just the rule of Lenity that is involved, but a public policy that Justice Marshal spoke of in United States versus Bass.", "start": 2366.825, "stop": 2378.299, "duration": 11.47, "cleanText": [["furthermore", "it", "be", "not", "just", "the", "rule", "of", "lenity", "that", "be", "involve", "but", "a", "public", "policy", "that", "justice", "marshal", "spoke", "of", "in", "united", "state", "versus", "bass"]]}, {"text": "It is so that this Court and any court can know exactly what it is that the man is being tried on, and that people know what they are being tried on.", "start": 2378.299, "stop": 2388.44, "duration": 10.14, "cleanText": [["it", "be", "so", "that", "this", "court", "and", "any", "court", "can", "know", "exactly", "what", "it", "be", "that", "the", "man", "be", "be", "try", "on", "and", "that", "people", "know", "what", "they", "be", "be", "try", "on"]]}, {"text": "When this statute says, and uses the language here,", "start": 2388.44, "stop": 2394.142, "duration": 5.7, "cleanText": [["when", "this", "statute", "say", "and", "use", "the", "language", "here"]]}, {"text": "\"whoever transports a forged document in interstate commerce. \"", "start": 2394.142, "stop": 2399.094, "duration": 4.95, "cleanText": [["whoever", "transport", "a", "forged", "document", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}, {"text": "and then Congress defines the words \"interstate commerce\" as meaning from state to state, it is clear what he looks at.", "start": 2399.094, "stop": 2406.95, "duration": 7.86, "cleanText": [["and", "then", "congress", "define", "the", "word", "interstate", "commerce", "as", "meaning", "from", "state", "to", "state", "it", "be", "clear", "what", "he", "look", "at"]]}, {"text": "The difference--", "start": 2406.95, "stop": 2407.85, "duration": 0.9, "cleanText": [["the", "difference"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, as has been suggested by some questions, must you show crossing a state line in interstate commerce?", "start": 2407.85, "stop": 2416.471, "duration": 8.62, "cleanText": [["well", "as", "have", "be", "suggest", "by", "some", "question", "must", "you", "show", "cross", "a", "state", "line", "in", "interstate", "commerce"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--Yes, Your Honor, for this.", "start": 2416.471, "stop": 2416.955, "duration": 0.48, "cleanText": [["yes", "your", "honor", "for", "this"]]}, {"text": "You do, because, Your Honor, you see, in 2315 Congress met that eventuality.", "start": 2416.955, "stop": 2424.344, "duration": 7.39, "cleanText": [["you", "do", "because", "your", "honor", "you", "see", "in", "congress", "meet", "that", "eventuality"]]}, {"text": "The situation posed by Justice White is clearly covered by 2315.", "start": 2424.344, "stop": 2431.998, "duration": 7.65, "cleanText": [["the", "situation", "pose", "by", "justice", "white", "be", "clearly", "cover", "by"]]}, {"text": "Again, I say that all the government failed to do in this case is charge under the right statute and the right section.", "start": 2431.998, "stop": 2440.337, "duration": 8.34, "cleanText": [["again", "i", "say", "that", "all", "the", "government", "fail", "to", "do", "in", "this", "case", "be", "charge", "under", "the", "right", "statute", "and", "the", "right", "section"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, but that argument... but 2314 and 2315 aren't mutually exclusive in their coverage, and there really is no reason to think that every statute Congress passes is mutually exclusive from another one.", "start": 2440.337, "stop": 2450.027, "duration": 9.69, "cleanText": [["well", "but", "that", "argument", "but", "and", "be", "not", "mutually", "exclusive", "in", "their", "coverage", "and", "there", "really", "be", "no", "reason", "to", "think", "that", "every", "statute", "congress", "pass", "be", "mutually", "exclusive", "from", "another", "one"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But it is in the same statute, Justice.", "start": 2450.027, "stop": 2452.562, "duration": 2.53, "cleanText": [["but", "it", "be", "in", "the", "same", "statute", "justice"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Well, but conceivably they could have been aiming at two slightly different things but there would have been some overlap.", "start": 2452.562, "stop": 2461, "duration": 8.44, "cleanText": [["well", "but", "conceivably", "they", "could", "have", "be", "aim", "at", "two", "slightly", "different", "thing", "but", "there", "would", "have", "be", "some", "overlap"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "But when they want to do that, Your Honor, I would suggest that they know how to do it.", "start": 2461, "stop": 2465.654, "duration": 4.65, "cleanText": [["but", "when", "they", "want", "to", "do", "that", "your", "honor", "i", "would", "suggest", "that", "they", "know", "how", "to", "do", "it"]]}, {"text": "They did it in the second paragraph of 2314.", "start": 2465.654, "stop": 2470.273, "duration": 4.62, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "it", "in", "the", "second", "paragraph", "of"]]}, {"text": "\"Whoever devises or plans to devise a scheme. \"", "start": 2470.273, "stop": 2474.427, "duration": 4.15, "cleanText": [["whoever", "devise", "or", "plan", "to", "devise", "a", "scheme"]]}, {"text": "and so forth.", "start": 2474.427, "stop": 2475.06, "duration": 0.63, "cleanText": [["and", "so", "forth"]]}, {"text": "And they have never amended that, and three circuits have read it that it is plain and clear that what it means is that under this particular paragraph, not even the whole section, just this same paragraph, it means what it says.", "start": 2475.06, "stop": 2492.056, "duration": 17, "cleanText": [["and", "they", "have", "never", "amend", "that", "and", "three", "circuit", "have", "read", "it", "that", "it", "be", "plain", "and", "clear", "that", "what", "it", "mean", "be", "that", "under", "this", "particular", "paragraph", "not", "even", "the", "whole", "section", "just", "this", "same", "paragraph", "it", "mean", "what", "it", "say"]]}, {"text": "The check has to be forged before its interstate transportation.", "start": 2492.056, "stop": 2496.674, "duration": 4.62, "cleanText": [["the", "check", "have", "to", "be", "forge", "before", "its", "interstate", "transportation"]]}, {"text": "If the government wants to charge somebody under both sections, there is no prohibition against that.", "start": 2496.674, "stop": 2503.161, "duration": 6.49, "cleanText": [["if", "the", "government", "want", "to", "charge", "somebody", "under", "both", "section", "there", "be", "no", "prohibition", "against", "that"]]}, {"text": "They could have charged him with four or five sections, and perhaps sustained a valid conviction.", "start": 2503.161, "stop": 2508.915, "duration": 5.75, "cleanText": [["they", "could", "have", "charge", "him", "with", "four", "or", "five", "section", "and", "perhaps", "sustain", "a", "valid", "conviction"]]}, {"text": "They didn't do it in this case, and now the man stands convicted of the third paragraph of 2314, and what the government is attempting to do, as I say, is stretch that language all out of proportion to what it was intended to cover because Congress already covered that in the Section 2315--", "start": 2508.915, "stop": 2531.281, "duration": 22.37, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "do", "it", "in", "this", "case", "and", "now", "the", "man", "stand", "convict", "of", "the", "third", "paragraph", "of", "and", "what", "the", "government", "be", "attempt", "to", "do", "as", "i", "say", "be", "stretch", "that", "language", "all", "out", "of", "proportion", "to", "what", "it", "be", "intend", "to", "cover", "because", "congress", "already", "cover", "that", "in", "the", "section"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Mr. White?", "start": 2531.281, "stop": 2531.964, "duration": 0.68, "cleanText": [["mr", "white"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "--and that is why the courts draw that distinction.", "start": 2531.964, "stop": 2534.399, "duration": 2.43, "cleanText": [["and", "that", "be", "why", "the", "court", "draw", "that", "distinction"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "UNKNOWN", "textObjs": [{"text": "Now, in Section 2312, which I tried to ask you about before, which deals with transporting in interstate commerce a motor vehicle or aircraft knowing it to have been stolen, in the Barfield case, the court placed the exact interpretation on that language which is parallel to that that we have here.", "start": 2534.399, "stop": 2554.296, "duration": 19.9, "cleanText": [["now", "in", "section", "which", "i", "try", "to", "ask", "you", "about", "before", "which", "deal", "with", "transport", "in", "interstate", "commerce", "a", "motor", "vehicle", "or", "aircraft", "know", "it", "to", "have", "be", "steal", "in", "the", "barfield", "case", "the", "court", "place", "the", "exact", "interpretation", "on", "that", "language", "which", "be", "parallel", "to", "that", "that", "we", "have", "here"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Thomas S. White", "textObjs": [{"text": "Yes.", "start": 2554.296, "stop": 2555.762, "duration": 1.47, "cleanText": [["yes"]]}, {"text": "You will notice that the Barfield case was decided by the Fifth Circuit Court of Appeals, the same court that decided Owens under 2314.", "start": 2555.762, "stop": 2566.551, "duration": 10.79, "cleanText": [["you", "will", "notice", "that", "the", "barfield", "case", "be", "decide", "by", "the", "fifth", "circuit", "court", "of", "appeal", "the", "same", "court", "that", "decide", "owen", "under"]]}, {"text": "The reason is that it was easily sustainable in Barfield as a continuation because the man was riding in the car, he was clearly chargeable under Section 2 as a principal, a fact that you don't have in this case.", "start": 2566.551, "stop": 2584.745, "duration": 18.19, "cleanText": [["the", "reason", "be", "that", "it", "be", "easily", "sustainable", "in", "barfield", "as", "a", "continuation", "because", "the", "man", "be", "rid", "in", "the", "car", "he", "be", "clearly", "chargeable", "under", "section", "as", "a", "principal", "a", "fact", "that", "you", "do", "not", "have", "in", "this", "case"]]}, {"text": "They didn't need any broad interpretation of 2312, because you have Section 2.", "start": 2584.745, "stop": 2591.935, "duration": 7.19, "cleanText": [["they", "do", "not", "need", "any", "broad", "interpretation", "of", "because", "you", "have", "section"]]}, {"text": "If I drive a car halfway across the state, and you and I are planning to drive a stolen car from Pittsburgh to Cleveland, and I do part of the driving and you do part of the driving to move it along, there is no question I am an aider and a better and a principal under Section 2.", "start": 2591.935, "stop": 2609.48, "duration": 17.55, "cleanText": [["if", "i", "drive", "a", "car", "halfway", "across", "the", "state", "and", "you", "and", "i", "be", "plan", "to", "drive", "a", "stolen", "car", "from", "pittsburgh", "to", "cleveland", "and", "i", "do", "part", "of", "the", "driving", "and", "you", "do", "part", "of", "the", "driving", "to", "move", "it", "along", "there", "be", "no", "question", "i", "be", "an", "aider", "and", "a", "good", "and", "a", "principal", "under", "section"]]}, {"text": "That clearly distinguishes Barfield from the case that we have here, and explains why the Fifth Circuit is the same court that drew this distinction.", "start": 2609.48, "stop": 2620.851, "duration": 11.37, "cleanText": [["that", "clearly", "distinguishes", "barfield", "from", "the", "case", "that", "we", "have", "here", "and", "explain", "why", "the", "fifth", "circuit", "be", "the", "same", "court", "that", "draw", "this", "distinction"]]}, {"text": "They would have held, under 2314, that it is necessary that it be a stolen... a stolen car, which it was in Barfield, that crossed the state line.", "start": 2620.851, "stop": 2632.393, "duration": 11.54, "cleanText": [["they", "would", "have", "hold", "under", "that", "it", "be", "necessary", "that", "it", "be", "a", "stolen", "a", "stolen", "car", "which", "it", "be", "in", "barfield", "that", "cross", "the", "state", "line"]]}, {"text": "Here, the question is, was it just a check or was it a forged check that crossed the state line, and that is the distinguishing factor in that case.", "start": 2632.393, "stop": 2642.701, "duration": 10.31, "cleanText": [["here", "the", "question", "be", "be", "it", "just", "a", "check", "or", "be", "it", "a", "forged", "check", "that", "cross", "the", "state", "line", "and", "that", "be", "the", "distinguish", "factor", "in", "that", "case"]]}]}, {"speakerName": "Warren E. Burger", "textObjs": [{"text": "Thank you, gentlemen.", "start": 2642.701, "stop": 2645.051, "duration": 2.35, "cleanText": [["thank", "you", "gentleman"]]}, {"text": "The case is submitted.", "start": 2645.051, "stop": 2645.986, "duration": 0.93, "cleanText": [["the", "case", "be", "submit"]]}]}]}], "decidedBy": "Burger Court", "arguedOn": "Jan 12, 1982", "petitioner": "McElroy", "respondent": "United States", "docket": "80-6680", "citation": "455US642(1982)", "justiaLink": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/455/642", "lowerCourt": "United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit", "grantedOn": "", "decidedOn": "Mar 23, 1982"}